title: dill pickles
directions: Boil and pour over tiny cucumbers that are packed in pint jars with a head of dill per jar.
Heat lids in boiling hot water. Have oven preheated to 350°.
After pickles are canned, set in pan in oven. Turn off heat.
Leave overnight.

title: pumpkin whoopies
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and oil.
Add pumpkin, flour, salt, baking powder, soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Sift together in bowl the first 4 ingredients.
Blend in blender the remaining ingredients.
Mix blended ingredients with dry until all dry is moistened.
Pour into buttered and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand in pan 5 minutes.
Turn out onto rack and cool.

title: adult wipes
directions: Mix the boiling water with the other ingredients.

title: sweet potato apple salad
directions: In a large bowl, gently toss first six ingredients.
Combine Cool Whip and mayonnaise; fold into fruit mixture.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Yield:
32 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Combine Ranch mix and salad oil.
Add dill weed, garlic powder and lemon pepper.
Pour over crackers and stir to coat.
Place on cookie sheet and place in 225° to 250° oven for 12 to 20 minutes. Cool before serving.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat after each.
Add coconut and pecans.
Mix.
Add vanilla wafers and milk alternately.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: broccoli with cheese sauce(microwave)
directions: In microwave, melt margarine for 30 seconds.
Stir in flour and seasonings until smooth.
Slowly stir in milk; microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir in cheese until melted (set aside).

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Add egg; cream until mixture is fluffy.
Stir into dry ingredients, until mixture is smooth.
Blend in milk.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of a water glass which has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: fruit tarts
directions: Cook apricots until tender (about 30 minutes) . Mash or puree apricots; add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil. Cool.
Roll pastry thin, cut 20 rounds (2 1/2-inch) with cookie cutter and 20 with a donut cutter of same size.
Place a rounded teaspoon of filling on middle of each round.
Moisten edge of pastry and seal donut rounds in place.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 425° oven.
Other fillings may be used.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: In large bowl, combine Jell-O and boiling water.
Stir until dissolved, then fold in all at once the strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Turn 1/2 of mixture into glass 13 x 9-inch dish as first layer.
Refrigerate until firm (about 1 hour).
Evenly spread top with sour cream mixed with Cool Whip.
Gently spoon on rest of mixture and refrigerate.

title: chow chow
directions: Put onions, tomatoes, cabbage and sweet and hot peppers through coarse blade of food grinder.
Add other ingredients. Cook until color changes.
Pack hot mixture into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal with new canning lids.

title: pistou soup
directions: In a soup tureen or large deep bowl (at least 3-quart) from which you serve the soup mix the first three ingredients.
Stir mixture well so oil coats basil.
Cover and let stand while you prepare the soup.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook diced potatoes in broth, celery, onion and bouillon cubes.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Add water to make as much soup as you want.

title: peach cornmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a large bowl cream butter and sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add the egg and beat well. In a separate bowl combine flour, cornmeal, salt, nutmeg and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add to butter mixture in two parts alternating with milk, stirring after each addition just until combined.
Add the fresh peaches and stir to blend.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full with the batter and bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 5 minutes on wire rack, gently remove from muffin tins and allow to cool completely.
Yield:
1 dozen.

title: cheese fruit mold
directions: Pour boiling water on gelatin, add sugar in large bowl, stir until gelatin and sugar is dissolved.
Beat in cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in pineapple (with syrup), Cheddar cheese, cottage cheese and lemon juice.
Pour into 12-cup mold.
Refrigerate until firm, about 8 hours.
Unmold onto salad greens and serve with Honey Dressing and crackers.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: In greased 2-quart casserole, place potatoes, green peppers and onions.
Use as much cheese as you prefer.
Add remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Top with cheese and bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken and season to taste.
Shred chicken.
Mix together chicken, cream cheese, soup and diced chilies.
Place a couple of spoonfuls of mixture across tortillas; add some shredded cheese and roll up.
Place each rolled up tortilla in cooking dish.
When dish is filled up, cover with enchilada sauce. Sprinkle more shredded cheese on top.
Place in 325° oven for approximately 15 minutes to melt cheese and heat up middle of the enchiladas.
Yummy!

title: chocolate-sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat margarine until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugars, beating 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until yellow disappears.

title: roast pheasant
directions: Thoroughly salt pheasant inside and out.
Fill cavity with bay leaf and celery leaves.
Wrap pheasant breast with bacon.
Secure in place with string.
Place pheasant in roaster.
Pour salad oil over pheasant.
Add mushrooms and onion slices.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Turn pheasant at 30 minute intervals, basting with drippings from pan.
Place on platter; remove string, celery leaves and bay leaf.
Garnish with spiced apples and parsley.

title: chocolate chess pies
directions: Stir first 6 ingredients together.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 300° until firm.

title: deer steak with tomatoes
directions: Layer ingredients, ending with the tomatoes. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pecan cranberry muffins
directions: In a bowl, toss cranberries with 1/4 cup sugar; set aside. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and remaining sugar.
Cut in butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine eggs and milk; stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Fold in pecans, lemon peel and cranberries.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until muffins test done.
Yield:
about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Remove rolls from containers and unroll to form strips.
Place lengthwise on a cookie sheet and pat to form pizza crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: spinach squares
directions: In a medium bowl, beat together until smooth the eggs, milk, butter, flour and baking powder.
Thoroughly stir in the spinach, green onion and cheese.
Turn into a buttered 8 x 8-inch cake pan; smooth the top.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until brown, 35 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Cut in small squares. Remove with a small spatula.
Top each square with a small piece of pimiento.
Serve warm as hors d'oeuvres.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll in chopped nuts and eat with Hi Ho crackers.

title: curried pork chops with oranges
directions: Trim separable fat from chops. Cut each chop in half.
Spray skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Preheat over medium-high heat. Add pork chops and brown on both sides.
Drain fat. Add orange juice, honey and curry powder to skillet.
Bring to boiling. Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until pork chops are tender and no longer pink.
Remove chops and keep warm.
Peel oranges. Slice crosswise, then half circular slices. Set aside.

title: pasta salad
directions: Pour on Italian salad dressing.
Stir.
Top with grated cheese.

title: spinach souffle
directions: In small heavy saucepan melt margarine.
Blend in flour; cook until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boil for 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir in spinach, onion, nutmeg and pepper.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold gently into spinach mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour into 1 3/4-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4, approximately 120 calories per serving.

title: ellie's chocolate milk
directions: Pour milk in your cup.
Stir in your chocolate.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail with juice, 1 cup coconut and eggs; blend and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, except substitute 1 cup of Coca-Cola for the water and add almond extract.
Pour into pan. Bake as directed.
Immediately frost with Coca-Cola frosting.

title: potato circle
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a skillet with 3 tablespoons butter.
Use a tight fitting cover for skillet.
Toss potatoes with salt and pepper.
Layer 1/3 of potato slices in a circle around bottom and sides of skillet.
Dot with butter.
Repeat 2 more times.
Over high heat, cook potatoes 3 minutes; then bake, covered, 30 minutes.
Place foil under skillet to catch overflow. Remove cover; bake 5 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Invert on a serving dish.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix pie filling with soda and milk.
Combine pumpkin, eggs, sugar and oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until golden brown about 10 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello and marshmallows in 1 cup hot boiling water. Add 1 cup cold water.
Cool until it starts to congeal, then whip with mixer.
Prepare Dream Whip and fold into jello.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple and nuts and fold in.

title: karen's hot bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off fat. Stir in the taco seasoning mix. Do not add water. Add can of refried beans. Mix well. Spread on the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix sour cream and green salsa. Spread over bean mixture. Grate Cheddar cheese and sprinkle on to cover generously. Bake at 375° about 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: butterscotch pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Gradually stir in liquids; add butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Take from heat; gradually stir half of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute more, stirring constantly. Take from heat; blend in vanilla.

title: dutch oven potatoes number 1
directions: In a
5-quart
Dutch
oven,
add
2 layers of potatoes, sliced onions and a portion of cream of mushroom soup.
Add 2 more layers
of
potatoes,
sliced
onions and a layer of the Cheddar cheese soup.
Alternate until 1-inch from top or less. Add
beer. Cook
at
325° until tender.
A little crushed red peppers in some of the layers is a treat.

title: fruit dip
directions: Add pudding to sour cream dry.
Blend all together.

title: ziti and cheese casserole
directions: Cook ziti according to package directions.
Drain.
In large bowl, combine cheeses, egg, salt and pepper.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer sauce, ziti and cheese filling, ending with sauce.
Bake 40 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: ham stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut the zucchini in half lengthwise.
Simmer in salted water for 10 minutes.
Scoop out the pulp; combine with the other ingredients.
Stuff the zucchini shells.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: dream fruit dip
directions: With mixer, cream the cream cheese until soft and smooth.
Add confectioners sugar and beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and blend just until combined.
Cover and chill several hours before serving.
Place in center of large platter and surround with variety of fresh fruit.

title: in-and-out-of-season fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruit in large, lettuce-lined bowl; toss gently to mix.
Serve dressing separately.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: pizza sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Prepare dough.
Roll dough to about 1/4-inch thick.
Using a sharp knife or pizza cutter, cut dough into narrow strips 1/2-inch wide.
Cut strips into 3-inch sticks. Dip sticks into melted butter and roll in mixture of Parmesan cheese, oregano and garlic salt.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet about 3/4 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 3 dozen sticks.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Mix together cream of celery soup, cheese, onions, peppers and chicken broth.
Put in saucepan on low heat for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Take off heat; stir in shredded chicken breast.
In casserole dish; crumble 1/2 bag of Doritos chips.
Pour mixture over chips; add remaining chips to top of mixture.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 350° or until chips on top are brown.

title: corn crisp chicken
directions: In a plastic bag, mix crumbs and seasonings.
Dip chicken pieces in milk.
Add to crumb mixture and shake to coat.
Place chicken, skin side up, in foil lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: whipped frosting
directions: Chill small mixer bowl and beaters in freezer.
Combine nondairy creamer and milk and whip at high speed until stiff peaks form, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add Sugar Twin and flavoring and blend.
Refrigerate.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: Mix bread, onion, celery, egg, garlic, salt and pepper. Crumble ground beef into mixture thoroughly.
Press into loaf dish, 9 x 5-inches.
Microwave at High (100%) until inner temperature reaches 150°, 17 to 20 minutes.
If oven other than Sharp Carousel, rotate meat loaf once or twice during cooking.
Spread with catsup. Microwave at Medium (50%) until catsup is heated, 2 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown ground beef; add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 1 hour.

title: orange-pineapple freeze
directions: In saucepan, mix water and sugar; heat to boiling.
Cook over medium heat from 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add orange juice and pineapple juice; freeze hard.
To serve, break in small pieces and stir until mushy.
Spoon into sherbets.
Trim with grated orange peel.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
In saucepan, combine juice, sugar and eggs.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Stir in pineapple, celery, apples and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Cover and freeze. Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: classic turkey salad
directions: In medium bowl, stir together mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together and bring to boil; pour into cooked pie crust.
Beat egg whites and add 1/3 cup sugar and teaspoon
vanilla
until
stiff;
put on pie and brown in oven.

title: savory salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 1/3 cup liquid; set aside.
Remove skin and bones from salmon, if desired.
Flake salmon with a fork. Brown 1 1/2 cups cracker crumbs in 1/4 cup butter in a large skillet; set mixture aside.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until done; drain water from potatoes.
Mix all other ingredients and mix enough mayonnaise to mix together.

title: potato salad
directions: Put potatoes in saucepan.
Add water.
Heat to boiling.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat until tender, 30 minutes.
Rinse with cold water.
Cut into eighths.
Put in large bowl.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Coat a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.

title: pecan fruit cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes on ungreased pan.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: baked shells
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cheese).
Place in greased casserole pan and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Put cheese on top and bake until cheese is melted.

title: dip
directions: Mix well.
Make 1 to 2 days in advance.
Use cauliflower, celery, carrots, cucumber, cherry tomatoes or green pepper with dip.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cool whip and jello. Add cottage cheese and mix well. Add drained fruit and mix. Then chill about 2-3 hours.

title: corn bread chicken and dressing
directions: In a large pot, cover chicken and chicken parts with water to make broth.
Add all chopped ingredients.
Season well to taste. Boil until done.
Remove chicken and debone.

title: english muffin loaves (2)
directions: Combine
3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda. Heat liquids to 125°.
Add to mixture and beat.
Stir in remaining 2 cups of flour to make a stiff batter.
Grease two microwave bread pans and sprinkle with cornmeal.
Spoon bread mixture in. Sprinkle additional cornmeal on top of loaves for color. Microwave on 10% power for 15 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Microwave on High 6 1/2 to 7 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pans.
Slice and toast.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Combine sugars, flour and cornmeal in a mixing bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine milk, vanilla, beaten eggs, vinegar and melted butter.
Stir liquid mixture gradually into dry ingredients until well blended.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 35 to 40 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: ranch-style salad dressing
directions: Mix well and let stand in refrigerator a few days to develop flavor before using.

title: pickled oysters
directions: Simmer the oysters in 3 pints of water for 20 minutes or until plump. Drain well and place in cold water to stop cooking. In a large pot (5-quart), put the vinegar, 3 pints water, sugar, pickling spice and bay leaves.
Cook 10 minutes on simmer. In a large bowl, layer oysters and sliced onions until all oysters are used.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over oysters.
Let cool before covering.
Refrigerate up to 4 months.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, blending well.
Add 1 cup hot water.
Mixture will be thin.
Bake in prepared pan in preheated oven for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp marinara
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion and garlic in hot oil, stirring occasionally, until onion is tender.
Cut up tomatoes. Add tomatoes and juice, basil and oregano to onion mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally, until most of the liquid is evaporated. Stir in shrimp.
Cook, stirring, for 5 minutes or until shrimp are done.
Serve garnished with fresh basil, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chili dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch deep dish plate or shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spread cream cheese in bottom of baking dish.
Mix chili and salsa until blended, then pour over cream cheese.
Sprinkle with Monterey Jack and Colby cheeses. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: christmas jello
directions: Mix the lime Jell-O with 2 cups hot water; dissolve and pour into a
9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Mix the pineapple Jell-O with 2
cups
hot water;
dissolve and let cool.
Cream the
cream cheese;
add
the
Cool
Whip.
Fold
in
pineapple Jell-O and pour
over	lime
Jell-O.
Let set overnight.
Dissolve the strawberry	Jell-O	and
2 cups hot water; let cool. Pour over Cool Whip mixture;	let set.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Put the tomatoes through a blender.
Should be 2 cups hot. Mix with jello and chill until set.
Nice in a mold.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Watch closely.
Then mix next two items and pour over top of baked layer.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Spread on top of coconut mixture.

title: cheese puff
directions: Place 3 slices of bread into the bottom of a greased baking dish. Sprinkle with half the cheese and cover with the rest of the bread.
Beat eggs; add milk and seasonings.
Pour over bread and cheese and cover with rest of cheese.
Set baking dish in a pan of hot water and bake at 350° (moderate oven) for about 40 minutes or until custard is set and bread is puffy.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Cut chicken breasts in thin strips.
Slightly beat egg and milk together.
Dip chicken in liquid mixture, then dip in flour seasoned with Season-All.
Repeat.

title: diabetic date nut cake
directions: Cream oleo; add egg, sweetener and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to first mixture with applesauce.
Add fruit and nuts.
Beat with mixer until well blended.
Bake in loaf pan lined with waxed paper or use Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: flag dessert
directions: Slice 1 cup of the strawberries; set aside.
Halve remaining strawberries; set aside.
Line bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish with cake slices.
Top with 1 cup sliced strawberries, 1 cup of the blueberries and all of the whipped topping.
Place strawberries halves and remaining 1/3 cup blueberries on whipped topping to create a flag design.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 15 servings.

title: ge' quiche
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef, sausage and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Microwave broccoli and spinach until done.
Add all ingredients together in large bowl.
Brown pie crust in oven for 10 minutes.
Then add all ingredients into pie crust.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zingy bacon bits
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Combine cream cheese, bacon, milk, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce in bowl.
Mix well.
Spread mixture on half the bread slices.
Top with remaining bread.
Cut each sandwich into thirds.
Serves 6.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, sugar and Kool-aid in hot water.
Add cold water.
Pour into molds and freeze.

title: salad for christmas
directions: Mix jello, water and pineapple juice.
Let cool.
Add pineapple, strawberries and pecans.
Put half mixture and let congeal; put sour cream on the rest of mixture and let congeal.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add flour salt, soda and mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 11 x 14 pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean when put into center.
May add sausage, brown and drain and add before baking.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat butter and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer until fluffy. Stir in corn syrup, oats and vanilla with wooden spoon.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add cream cheese and whip with mixer; refrigerate until firm.
Add fruit and Cool Whip and mix. Refrigerate again until firm.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine butter, shortening and sugar; beat until smooth.
Beat egg yolks; add to mixture.
Combine flour, soda, vanilla, buttermilk and egg whites; add to mixture.
Fold in the coconut and nuts.
You may wish to save some of the coconut to go on the frosting.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 3 layers or 1 oblong cake.

title: gerbeaud squares
directions: Mix 1 cup walnuts and sugar together and set aside.
Sift flour, baking soda, 1 tablespoon sugar and salt into bowl.
Cut butter into flour.
Add eggs, yeast cake and sour cream.
Knead together well.
Divide into 4 parts.
Roll one part of the dough to fit a 14 x 12-inch pan.
Put in bottom of pan.
Spread thinly with apricot preserves or raspberry jam.
Sprinkle sugared walnuts over preserves (about 1/3 of the walnuts).
Roll second dough to fit top of walnuts.
Spread again with jam.
Sprinkle with sugared walnuts again.
Roll third dough to fit top
of walnuts.
Spread again with jam.
Sprinkle with sugared walnuts again.
Roll fourth dough and put on top of walnuts.
Place in warm place and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cool, spread with chocolate icing.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet with onions and garlic. Drain off excess fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, celery and mushrooms.
Add sugar, oregano, basil and salt.
Bring to a boil and boil uncovered 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove sauce from heat and stir in spaghetti.
Spread half of this mixture in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Add rest of mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: larry's clam chowder
directions: Cook together margarine and flour on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add milk slowly. Stir constantly.
In separate pan, cook clams, onion and potatoes until potatoes are tender.
Mix potato mixture with milk mixture. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate top cookies
directions: Cream the butter and both sugars well.
Stir in the egg yolks. Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir well and put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool 10 minutes and frost with topping.

title: holiday cranberry relish
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil for about 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except cognac.
Cook over low heat until cranberries start popping.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat. Add cognac and chill.
Recipe may be doubled or tripled.

title: easy and good roast beef
directions: Mix
soups together.
Put roast in large pot (ovenproof with lid).
Pour soup mixture over roast.
Do not salt.
Cook at 300° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: noodles and cabbage
directions: In a heavy frying pan, melt margarine (the amount depends on the amount of cabbage and noodles).
Add the lightly salted cabbage and cook until almost done.
Meantime, cook the noodles.
Drain the noodles and add the cabbage, sprinkle lightly with caraway seed. If you like cabbage, use more cabbage and less noodles.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove from heat and add flour, salt and pepper, stirring to form a smooth paste.
Gradually add milk, stirring as you add to make a smooth mixture.
Cook over low heat until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add 2 cups cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: salt pickles
directions: Heat all ingredients until color changes.
Put in jar and seal.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Combine in saucepan the sugar, salt, nutmeg, cloves, cinnamon and water.
Boil syrup to soft ball stage.
Add nuts and stir until sugary.
Pour on greased pan.

title: fastnaughts (shrove cakes)
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add shortening and eggs.
Add milk. Put on board and knead a little.
Roll out, not quite as thin as pie crust.
Cut in squares and make a small slit in the middle. Fry in deep fat.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: spanish breakfast
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients together; drain.
Add eggs; scramble together.
Add remaining ingredients and cook.
Serve with hash browns or refried beans.

title: tuna spins
directions: Combine Bisquick mix and milk.
Stir with fork until mixed. Roll into a square on floured board.
Combine tuna and soup. Spread evenly on dough; roll up and slice like cinnamon rolls.

title: savory cauliflower
directions: Cut cone shape wedge out of cauliflower core.
Place cauliflower and 1/4 cup water in a 1 1/2-quart microproof casserole.
Cover and cook on High (maximum power) for 9 minutes; drain.
Mix mayonnaise, onion, mustard and salt.
Spoon sauce over cauliflower.
Lay cheese slices on top.
Cook, uncovered, on 70% power (roast) for 1 minute or until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: easy cabbage
directions: Put drippings into skillet.
Cut up cabbage into serving size pieces.
Put 7-Up in with drippings.
Add cabbage; cover and cook until tender.

title: chicken-almond salad
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water; dissolve over hot water.
Cool slightly; combine mayonnaise, whipped cream, and salt.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill in molds until firm.
Unmold on lettuce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Melt shortening in large skillet. Coat chicken with flour; cook in hot shortening until brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Set aside.

title: tomato and basil sauce
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes.
Peel and chop garlic, then saute garlic in oil until golden.
Add tomatoes quickly to avoid splattering.
Mix the basil with the tomato mixture.
Cook on low for one half hour.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Toss with favorite pasta.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into the pie shell. Refrigerate four or more hours.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Brown chicken in skillet.
Place in casserole.
Combine soups, rice and water.
Pour over rice.
Place in oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salami bakes hors d'oeuvre
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place salami slices on cookie sheet and sprinkle with grated cheese mix.
Bake until browned.
Place on paper towel to absorb grease and let cool.
Serves 8.

title: party ham biscuits
directions: Slice (or split) rolls.
Mix first 5 ingredients and spread on rolls.
Cover with ham and cheese.
Place top on rolls.
When ready to serve, bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to directions.
When cool, prick holes in brownies and pour liqueur on top.
Let stand overnight, then crumble the brownies into pieces.

title: mom's spanish beans
directions: Drain green string beans.
Place in baking pan, 8 x 8-inch. Sprinkle with approximately 1/4 cup brown sugar.
Dab with ketchup.
Cover with onion and bacon.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: barbecue pot roast
directions: Marinate roast overnight in everything but barbecue sauce. Cook on low all day in crock-pot.
When done, add barbecue sauce.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in melted oleo and then in crumbs.
Coat chicken heavily.
Place breasts in a baking dish and bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes uncovered.
(Can be prepared the day before and refrigerated, then baked.
It also freezes well.)
Serves 6.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Crush wafers and add to mixture alternately with milk.
Add coconut and pecans.
Add vanilla. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: cherry krisp
directions: Place cherries in a 9 x 12-inch buttered baking dish.
Cut low-fat margarine evenly into cake mix.
Sprinkle evenly over cherries.
Add nuts to cake mix mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spicy pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (8 x 4-inch) loaf pans.
In medium bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients.
Set aside.
In large bowl of electric mixer, beat eggs until frothy; beat in oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in flour, zucchini and pineapple.
Divide by pouring 1/2 of the batter in each prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour or until tests done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; turn out and cool on wire racks.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Mix hot water and jello in large mixing bowl.
Add pineapple, cranberry sauce, nuts, orange sections and peel.
Mix well.
Add gelatin and water last and stir evenly.
Congeal.

title: oat bran muffins(low cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Line muffin cups with paper liners or coat with vegetable oil.

title: serendipity
directions: Melt first 2 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cool.
Add cashew nuts and Chinese noodles.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper and let cool.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Cook fruit until thickened.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add salad oil and milk.
Pour over cooked fruit.
Pour boiling water over it.
Cook for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: brown rice
directions: Combine all
ingredients in a 3 quart casserole; cover. Microwave on High
minutes.
Reduce power to Medium; microwave until liquid is
absorbed
and
rice
is tender, 25 to 35 minutes. Fluff with fork before serving.

title: chili
directions: Fry onions and green peppers separately in oil until soft. Add a little water and continue cooking 15 minutes.
Fry turkey or beef in oil until red is gone.
Add a little water and continue cooking for 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and kidney beans (prefer Raggedy Ann brand).
Place tomatoes and kidney beans in a kettle; cook until hot.
Add onions, green peppers and meat.
Add red pepper and some salt.
Add chili powder.
Cook 1 hour.
Add water, if needed.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Tear cooked chicken into bite-size pieces.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour ingredients into one pie shell.
Place the other pie shell on top and mash the edges together with a fork.
Bake at 375° until top crust is brown.

title: biscuit barbecue cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown ground beef in a large skillet, then drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onions and brown sugar.
Cook 1 minute to blend flavors.
Stir constantly.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits and place them into the muffin pan.
Firmly press biscuit down inside the pan and up along the sides. Spoon about 1/4 cup of the meat mixture into each biscuit.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute, then remove from pan.

title: tuna and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in 2 quarts boiling salt water until soft.
Drain well and rinse.
Peel and slice eggs.
Drain oil off tuna and discard.
Arrange layers of noodles, sliced eggs, flaked tuna and peas in a greased 6-cup casserole, beginning and ending with noodles.
Heat mushroom soup and add liquid from drained peas or milk to fill mushroom soup can.
Stir together; heat to boiling. Pour over the tuna and noodles mixture in the casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and bake in a hot oven at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until cheese is brown.
Makes 5 servings.

title: lincoln lee pudding
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan (or smaller). Drop dumplings in sauce.
Bake at 500° for 20 to 25 minutes. Dumplings will puff up.
A wonderful, quick and very old recipe.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples and let
stand
for 1 hour.
Mix eggs, vanilla and oil together and
add
to
apples and sugar; mix well. Add salt, flour and soda.
Mix well, then add nuts. Bake in loaf or tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy cookies
directions: In bowl, mix peanut butter, margarine, vanilla and sugar with hands.
It may be very stiff and crumbly.
Make little balls. Place on cookie sheet that has been lined with wax paper and refrigerate.
In double boiler, melt chocolate and shortening. When smooth, pour into a small bowl.
Dip balls in chocolate with a toothpick.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes or freeze.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add vegetables and soup. Place mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle top with Tater Tots. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice a layer of squash to
cover
the	bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover
this
with
a	layer
of
onions. Repeat.
Mix 2 cans of soup
together and pour over squash and onions.
Bake for approximately
minutes
Remove from oven and cover with cracker crumbs and margarine mixture. Bake 10 minutes more and remove from oven.

title: ham in a garden
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, heat the butter and add the onion and green pepper, sauteing until onion is light brown. Add the garlic and saute for 2 more minutes. Add the remaining ingredients except the okra, adjust the heat so the mixture is simmering and allow to simmer for 5 minutes. Add the okra and cook for another 10 minutes. Serves 2.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Peel and slice apples; set aside.
Mix 3 tablespoons of sugar with 2 teaspoons of cinnamon; set aside.
Mix the eggs with sugar. Add oil, vanilla, orange juice, baking powder and flour.
Mix well until smooth and thick.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Alternate layers of batter, apples and cinnamon/sugar mixture 3 times.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool well before removing from pan.

title: almond jubilee squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix cookie dough (don't use mixer and don't beat).
Spread on ungreased large cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Batter is very thick.
Cook for about 15 minutes.

title: camper's special
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place first 3 ingredients in order.
Dot with butter, then sprinkle with pecans over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Cook bacon in a large saucepan until crisp.
Remove bacon; drain on paper towels.
In bacon drippings, cook onions and garlic until soft.
Add water, black-eyed peas, rice, bay leaf, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 to 1/2 hours or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Crumble bacon into rice mixture; stir.
Sprinkle with fresh snipped parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: green veggie bake
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add cornstarch, salt, pepper and sour cream; mix well.
Stir in green vegetables.
Put in casserole dish (8 x 8-inch is good) and top with grated cheese.

title: orange walnut bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine eggs, butter, orange juice, orange peel and water.
Add all at once to flour mixture and stir quickly until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in walnuts.
Put into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in 9 x 13 pan.
While still warm, poke holes in cake with the handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour Eagle brand milk over cake, then repeat with caramel topping. Refrigerate 6 hours.
Frost with whipped topping or whipped cream and sprinkle with Heath and Hershey bars.

title: fried fish
directions: Melt Crisco in Frydaddy, preferably to the line.
Put Hi Ho crackers in a Ziploc bag.
Beat crackers until they're real fine. Put in a bowl and set aside.
Mix eggs and milk in a separate bowl.
Dip fish in milk and eggs; salt each side of fish.
Dip in cracker crumbs.
Cook in Crisco for about 3 to 4 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken, seasoned with bouillon; cool, debone and chop. Place celery, pimento, dill cubes, bell pepper and eggs into blender. Chop fine and mix other ingredients; chill and serve with favorite crackers.

title: on the wing chicken sauce (great for steak, too!)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate a few hours or overnight.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water until tender.
Place spaghetti and chicken in alternate layers in a 3-quart casserole. Brown celery, onion and pepper in a small amount of oleo 10 minutes. Add soups and water.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Add olives.
Pour sauce over chicken and spaghetti.
Heat in oven at 350°. Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 8.

title: cherry cake (pound or 13 x 9)
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add with milk.
Add chopped cherries and juice.
Pour batter into greased and floured pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours for pound cake or 1 hour in a 13 x 9-inch pan, until done.

title: mock champagne punch
directions: I served this at my two daughters weddings.
Everyone raved about it.
It is so easy and good.

title: pineapple-cheese salad with creamy topping
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin; add cold water.
Chill until begins to thicken.
Drain pineapple; save syrup for topping. Sprinkle cheese into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Fold pineapple and bananas into thickened gelatin.
Spoon over cheese. Chill until firm.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast in one strip of bacon.
In an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan, place a layer of dried beef. Place bacon wrapped chicken on top of this.
Combine soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in a slow oven (275°) for 2 hours.
Uncover and continue baking another 30 minutes. (This makes it great to put in the oven before church!)
Serve over rice or egg noodles.
This isn't low calorie, but then it's for a party!

title: mama's patty stew
directions: Mix ground beef with egg, dry milk powder, cracker crumbs or oatmeal and salt and pepper.
(This is the way people cooked in mama's day.)
Brown patties, pour off drippings and turn heat down to simmer.
Add couple tablespoons of water, carrots, celery, diced onion and parsley.
Let simmer for 30 minutes, covered.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Gently boil zucchini for 15 minutes on low heat.
Stir often. Add sugar and boil 6 more minutes.
Stir often.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O; mix well.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in bottom of pan.
Mix soup and milk together; pour over chicken.
Prepare stuffing (moist) and spoon over top of soup and chicken.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mother hendrix's potato pie
directions: Stir until smooth; pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake until crust is brown and filling is firm.

title: baked apple doughnuts *
directions: Mix together first eight ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While hot, dip in melted oleo and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: apricot lemon chiffon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Combine flour and sugar. Stir to mix. Combine eggs, yogurt, preserves, and melted butter. Beat until well blended. Add to flour mixture and beat until well mixed. Spoon into well greased muffin tin, filling each cup 2/3 full. Bake for 13 to 18 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of one of the muffins. Makes 12 muffins.

title: bacon cheese potatoes
directions: Cook peeled tomatoes until tender but firm.
Drain and cube. Mix potatoes, onion, cheese and mayo.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with bacon; cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through and cheese melts. Sprinkle with cilantro before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine salad dressing and preserves; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Serve with assorted fruit dippers.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve cold with bread.
Use Hawaiian or sourdough bread.
You can hollow the center of the bread and place the dip in the center.
The chunks of bread that you have removed from the center can be placed around the outside of the serving dish.

title: microwave egg drop soup
directions: Mix broth, water, onion and soy sauce in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover.
Microwave at High (100%) until mixture boils, 8 to 10 minutes.
Pour eggs into mixture, stirring gently until eggs form strings.
Serve with can fried noodles with green onions (optional).

title: corn pudding
directions: Spray dish with Pam; add corn mixture. Bake in water bath at 350° for 1 hour.

title: braised spareribs
directions: Wipe spareribs with a damp cloth; cut into serving portions. Dip in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot bacon drippings.
Reduce heat.
Add water; cover and simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
If preferred, place browned spareribs in baking pan with water.
Cover and bake in a moderately slow oven (325°).
Serves 5.

title: meal in a bowl
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Add beef broth, cream-style corn, diced potatoes, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Cover and cook on low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.
Tastes very good.

title: gelatine blocks
directions: In a large bowl, mix unflavored gelatine and jello; add boiling water and stir until completely dissolved.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan; chill until firm.
When firm, cut into 1 inch squares. Makes about 9 dozen blocks.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls together on square cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 or 9 minutes or until brown.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados.
Squeeze lemon juice over top and stir.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Adjust seasonings to personal liking.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Heat to melt the first four ingredients in saucepan.
Mix next three ingredients in a bowl.
Pour melted ingredients into dry ingredients in bowl.
Beat well, adding milk, eggs and baking soda. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: home made chocolates
directions: To make fillings:
mix together condensed milk, confectioners sugar, and oleo margarine.
Divide into 4 small bowls and flavor as desired (almond, lemon, peanut butter, unsweetened chocolate, oil of peppermint).
Roll into small balls and put in a cold place until they crust over, (just a few minutes).
To finish the chocolates, melt in a double boiler 2 packages chocolate bits, 4 squares unsweetened chocolate, 1/2 block paraffin wax, (Yes wax!). That is 1/2 block.
There are many blocks in a package.
With tongs or forks, dip each piece in the chocolate and put on wax paper to cool.
Put in a cool place until they harden.
With left over chocolate, dip maraschino cherries, walnuts, raisins, Kraft Caramels, Rice Crispies, etc.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine cooked chicken, Veg-All, soup and milk in a large bowl, then place in pie shell. Place other pie shell on top and cut several slits in it.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: mostaccioli with tomatoes
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine olive oil, vinegar and garlic.
Add 1/2 of the basil and blend one minute.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over warm mostaccioli.
Add tomatoes and toss. Garnish with remaining basil leaves.
Makes approximately 4 quarts.
Only 5 grams of fat per cup!

title: bloody mary dip
directions: In medium bowl, blend soup mix with sour cream.
Stir in vodka and hot sauce.
Serve with celery sticks.
Makes 2 cups of dip.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in an oiled casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: waffles
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in buttermilk and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Add melted butter (and nuts, if desired).
Blend well.
Allow batter to rest for at least 1 hour.
It can be refrigerated overnight.
Bake in preheated waffle iron.

title: marinated mushrooms(appetizer)
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over mushrooms.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight. Drain.
Serve as appetizer or spoon on top of salad greens and serve as a salad.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump into 8 x 13 x 2-inch pan the pineapple and cherry mix. Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Sprinkle 1 cup pecans over cake mix. Slice 2 sticks butter or margarine on top of everything.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian cream fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and corn syrup over medium heat to 252° (using candy thermometer). Stir occasionally to prevent scorching. Remove from heat. Add margarine. Do not stir. Let set approximately 20 minutes. Add vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer until it gets really thick and creamy. Stir in nuts. Pour into 2 buttered loaf pans. Cool until firm. Store in refrigerator overnight. Cut and wrap.

title: hawaiian sherbet
directions: Mix and freeze per ice cream freezer directions.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients together and press into a 13 x 9 pan very firmly. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta.
Drain.
Add olive oil and toss lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss and refrigerate approximately 3 hours to allow to marinate.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening.
Add eggs and blend well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla. Pour in greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: homemade tamales
directions: Recipe is for approximately 5 dozen.

title: pepper steak
directions: Using a large frying pan or stir-fry pan, cook steak in oil until brown.
Add 1 cup or so of water, cover and cook until tender (replacing water, if necessary).

title: tuna-macaroni bake
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Add soup, milk, tuna, lemon rind, pepper, seasoning salt and 2 cups cheese.
Mix well.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Cover with potato chips mixed with remaining cheese.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 40 minutes.
This can be frozen.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken soup

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add vanilla.
Spread over top of cake, put on rest of Cool whip and chill.

title: spring soup (potage printanier)(makes 6 servings)
directions: Melt the butter in a stock pot and saute onions and leeks until soft but not brown.
Add potatoes, carrots, salt and 5 cups of water.
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes after boiling.
Add rice and asparagus (or beans or peas) and cook for 25 minutes (until rice is cooked).
Add spinach and cook about 1 minute.
Add milk or cream; heat and serve.
(I think this always tastes better the second day.)

title: potato souffle
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add pecans and mix well.
Spread over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Mix meat, water, salt, pepper, onion and tomato paste.
Cut the tops off the peppers and clean out the seeds.
Stuff peppers. Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add salt, eggs, vanilla and cream of tartar and beat well.
Sift the flour and soda together and add.
Knead like pie dough.
Shape into roll; slice and bake.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In
a
greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish spread out rice. Place chicken pieces on top of rice.
Mix water with soup and warm over low heat.
Stir until soup isn't lumpy.
Remove from heat
and pour
soup	over chicken and rice mixture.	Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
I use Pam to grease my dish with.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Dump in undrained pineapple; swirl it around to even it in pan.
Dump in pie filling and smooth it around until layers of fruit are even.
Sprinkle it with dry cake mix to cover the fruit evenly.
Melt butter; drizzle over top of this mixture, or distribute bits of solid margarine or butter evenly over the top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° until brown, or about 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream, ice cream or other topping.

title: never fail brownies(makes large batch)
directions: Heat butter and cocoa until butter melts (may be done in microwave), set aside.
Mix in large mixing bowl the eggs (beaten) and the sugar.
Add flour and vanilla; mix well.
Add butter/cocoa mixture and mix until blended.
Stir in pecans (if desired).
Pour into jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: chicken barbecue
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat chicken with flour, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in shortening.
Transfer to large casserole dish or pot which can be put into oven.
Saute onion in vegetable oil.
Add chopped celery, green peppers, ketchup, water, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Pour mixture over chicken in casserole.
Cover casserole and bake in oven for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate delight cake
directions: Cream the butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Melt chocolate in water and add vanilla.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Beat well. Take out 3 cups and set aside for frosting.
To the other part, add the 1/4 cup butter.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and soda and add to the egg-sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Spoon batter evenly into three greased 9-inch pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
After cake has cooled, put layers together with reserved sugar mixture.
Nuts may be added to frosting.

title: chicken casserole delicious
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces.
Place 2 tablespoons cut up chicken in center of a crescent roll, roll up starting with the wide end and place in baking dish.
Mix chicken soup, broth and cheese and pour over rolls.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: volie's cabbage rolls
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together in a bowl and prepare the cabbage leaves.
Wilt the cabbage leaves.
Place some of the meat mixture in each leaf and roll up.
Secure with a toothpick.
Put into a large Dutch oven.
Pour the tomato juice over the rolls. Add chili powder.
Boil gently for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cola cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour together.
In saucepan, combine butter, shortening, cocoa and cola; heat to boiling.
Add marshmallows and stir until dissolved.
Add buttermilk, soda and vanilla extract. Mix well and add to flour and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in well-greased and floured oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: In large glass, crumble beef.
Heat 2 to 3 minutes on high heat until brown, stirring once.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.
Combine cottage cheese, egg and pepper.
In oblong baking dish, spoon 1/2 cup sauce.
Alternately layer noodles, egg mixture, Mozzarella and meat sauce, forming 2 layers.
Heat 8 minutes on High (turning once) until noodles are tender.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Let stand covered 15 minutes before serving.

title: marinated octopus(my fathers recipe prepared every christmas eve)
directions: Boil
water; place octopus in salted water and cook for 5 minutes.
Cover
and let sit 30 minutes off of heat.
Drain and cool.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place in shallow bowl and add
the rest of the ingredients.
Toss and allow to marinate at least 2 hours before serving.
This will stay in refrigerator
for several
months.
This is wonderful as an appetizer. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and cold water into a large saucepan and cook until it forms a soft ball.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Pour in 1/2 of syrup mixture and continue cooking other half until it reaches a hard ball stage.
Add egg whites to mix and vanilla.
Continue beating until candy is thick enough to drop from spoon.
Drop 1 spoonful at a time onto wax paper and allow to cool.
Cover and store in an airtight container.

title: nacho salad
directions: Layer chips, cottage cheese, salsa, lettuce, tomato and onion on serving plate.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Makes 1 serving.

title: quick popsicles
directions: Combine
juice and syrup together until well blended.
Pour into popsicle molds and freeze until firm.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat
in
a
large
skillet,
drain.
Stir in the tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, diced onions, garlic salt, black pepper,
oregano
and
sugar.
Blend
well.
Cover
and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water according to package directions.
Add oil, stir occasionally. Drain,
rinse, drain again and separate noodles.

title: meatless burgers
directions: Add soy sauce, oil, chopped onions and minced garlic to boiling water.
Mix oats, sage, food yeast and nuts together. Sprinkle gradually into broth and let stand until liquid is absorbed.
Stir lightly until mixed.
Brown in small amount of oil until well done.

title: fresh fruit crisp
directions: Place rhubarb on bottom of ungreased 9-inch square baking pan. Sprinkle gelatin over fruit.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon.
Mix bacon, onions and cheese in large bowl.
In small bowl mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Don't add mayonnaise dressing to broccoli salad until just prior to serving.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon together twice.
Blend beaten eggs and sugar.
Add pumpkin and oil.
Blend. Add flour mixture and nuts.
Bake in 350° oven.
For large cake, bake about one hour.
For loaf pans bake about 50 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice and dry onion soup over bottom of pan.
Place browned chops over rice.
Mix mushroom soup and water.
Pour over chops and rice; cover pan with foil. Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until rice is tender.

title: zing
directions: For a milder sauce, remove seeds from peppers.
Caution:
When chopping or seeding peppers, wear rubber gloves.
Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Place small amounts at a time in blender and blend until smooth.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Great on meat, chicken or whatever you want to spice up.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add soups, water and Cheez Whiz.
Bring to a boil until cheese melts.
Add the uncooked rice and broccoli.
Salt to taste.
Bake in baking dish for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: quiche
directions: Break eggs into mixing bowl with cheeses, milk and salt. Blend with mixer until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and blend until smooth.
Pour into pie shells and bake in 350° oven until just set and crusts are lightly browned, 18 to 20 minutes. Cut in wedges and serve.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add ginger ale and chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in peaches, pecans and celery. Turn into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Use grapefruit and oranges with orange Jell-O for change.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Prepare chicken and place in crock-pot.
Pour in remaining ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on medium heat until chicken is done.

title: hot roast beef sandwich(leftover)
directions: Cut bread in half.
Cover with meat, then cover all with gravy.
Serve with creamed or baked potato and salad.

title: lemon snow bars
directions: Mix together butter, 1 1/3 cups flour, 1/4 cup sugar.
Pat into 8-inch square pan.
Bake near center of oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, or until brown on edges.

title: aunt roosie's rolls
directions: Combine yeast, 1/2 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar and let rise until makes 1 cup.
In a large bowl, mix 1 cup hot water, shortening, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and flour.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Knead until elastic, about 10 minutes.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Make into rolls.
Let rise and bake at 350°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Heat shortening in deep kettle to 375°.
Add oil to eggs. Combine flour, baking powder, sugar, onion powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture with parsley and corn.
Drop spoonfuls into hot fat.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes, turning to brown evenly.
Drain on paper towels.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown ground beef and add to remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: tomato delight
directions: Spread salad dressing on 1 side of each slice bread.
Layer tomato slices, salt and pepper on 2 slices bread.
Top with remaining bread.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Place on serving plate.
Pour milk into glass and serve.
This is especially good with German Johnson tomatoes.
Yield:
1 serving.

title: lime-orange punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir until dissolved.
When ready to serve, pour over ice.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Make cake mix according to directions in 9 x 13 pan. When cool, punch holes in cake with end of a wooden spoon. Put pineapple and sugar in saucepan and boil for five minutes. Then cool. Pour over cake. mix pudding and pour over pineapple. Slice bananas and place on cake over pudding. Top with nondairy whipped topping. Sprinkle with coconut and pecans. Yummy!

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease casserole dish with butter.
Place cooked broccoli in casserole dish. Tear chicken into small pieces and layer over broccoli.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients (except crumbs).
Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch Pyrex.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Fill greased and floured muffin tins (Pam works fine) 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 regular size muffins.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Add rest of ingredients (except lettuce) and mix well.
Freeze in muffin tins.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, margarine, cheese and seasoning and minced onion and then add to the hash browns.
Mix corn flakes and 1/2 stick of melted margarine and sprinkle on the top of casserole.

title: quail in a bag
directions: Salt and pepper the quail.
Place in a large cooking bag. Sprinkle with flour.
Add mushrooms, parsley, onions, water, garlic and bell peppers.
Close bag and prick top.
Cook one hour in a 350° oven.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain.
Place in heavy pan.
Add fresh or canned tomatoes.
Add tomato juice to cover.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
When cooked down," add cooked macaroni and stir to mix.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt oleo; put 3 tablespoons flour for roux; make color of peanut butter.
Put onions and garlic in roux until wilted; then add
soup
and
lower
fire;
add
salt, pepper, juice of lemon. Put
crab
meat
and simmer 10 minutes.
Add onion top and parsley and cook 10 minutes.

title: my chili recipe
directions: Melt fat
in
bottom of heavy skillet or saucepan.
Add onions, green pepper, celery and garlic.
Cook until partially tender,
stirring frequently.
Add beef; fry, uncovered, until lightly browned.
(I like to fry beef separately and drain fat before
adding
to vegetables.) Add tomatoes and chili powder. Add salt
and sugar.
Add Worcestershire and Tabasco to taste, some like it hot.
Cover; bring to a boil, then turn down heat and simmer about 1 hour, until thickened.

title: persimmon roll
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed and mix.
Spoon about 1/3 of mixture on sheet of waxed paper.
Shape in roll.
Makes 3 rolls.

title: grandma's crumb cake
directions: Cook box of raisins until plump.
Use just enough water to almost cover the raisins in a small pan.
Let cool.
Rub together brown sugar, white sugar and Crisco (save out about 1 cup of mixture for topping).
Beat until foamy 2 cups buttermilk (or sour milk) with 2 teaspoons of baking soda.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg (and others if desired).
Add sugar mixture to flour with milk.
Stir well.
Add raisins.
Mix well.
Pour into 1 large and 1 small greased and floured pans.
Add sugar topping. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry loaf(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add egg.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Slice rolls in half.
Melt margarine and add onion, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and poppy seed (if used).
Brush on both inside layers of rolls.
Layer ham and cheese on bottom layers. Cover with top layers of rolls.
Spread remaining sauce over rolls.
Cover with foil. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: apple squares
directions: Combine salt and flour.
Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Blend yolks, lemon juice and cold water; blend into flour mixture.
Divide mixture into two equal parts; set aside one part.
Roll other part to fit bottom and halfway up sides of a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: chinese cucumber salad
directions: Peel and seed cucumbers.
Cut in half lengthwise and slant dice.
Mix all other ingredients and put in refrigerator to chill. When ready to serve, pour sauce over cucumbers.
Mix well and serve.

title: marty's oven new potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and put in ovenproof casserole (peel a ring around potatoes).
Spray potatoes with cooking spray or pour melted butter over.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Bake at 350° until tender with lid on casserole.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° in three 8-inch layer pans for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Combine flour, milk, egg, margarine, pudding and baking powder.
Mix together for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch round pan or a 10-inch pie plate.
Layer drained peach slices over the batter.
Combine cream cheese, peach juice and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed; pour over peaches and batter.
Combine the cinnamon and 1 teaspoon sugar to make cinnamon sugar and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage corn bread
directions: In large bowl with fork, combine sausage and parsley.
Cook, covered, on High for 4 to 5 minutes until sausage just turns brown, stirring every minute.
In another bowl, stir together flour, cornmeal and baking powder.
Stir in milk, honey, carrot and eggs, then stir in sausage mixture.
Pour sausage mixture into greased 8 cup ring mold or Bundt pan.
Cook on High 10 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn every 2 minutes.
Let stand, 5 to 10 minutes.
With small spatula, loosen edges and turn onto warm plate.
Serves 8.

title: sweet cabbage and kielbasa
directions: Cut cabbage into quarters and then cut the quarters into 1/2 slices and then cut slices in half crossways to make bite size pieces.
Place butter first into a large covered heavy metal skillet or kettle type pan.
Add cabbage and garlic powder and salt and pepper for flavor.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: About 1 hour before serving, in 13 x 9-inch pan, spread 1 cup sour cream and set aside.
In 2-quart saucepan, flake chicken; add 1/2 cup sour cream, green chiles, onion, chili powder, salt, garlic power and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally. Preheat oven to 450°.
In 8-inch skillet with 1/2-inch salad oil, fry each tortilla a few seconds on each side, or until soft. Spread 1/2 cup chicken mixture along center of each tortilla.
Fold sides over filling and place seam side down in sour cream in pan. Spread enchiladas with remaining sour cream, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: vinaigrette
directions: Mix well and chill the vinaigrette.
Serve with cold meats or heat it and pour over broccoli, artichokes or asparagus.
A vinegar sauce on vegetables or meats is a nice touch for a hot, summer day.

title: tourtiere turnovers
directions: Cut butter into flour with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add sour cream and stir with a fork just until blended.
Dough will be quite soft.
Shape into a ball. Wrap and chill at least 2 hours.

title: applesauce cinnamon bread(for bread machine)
directions: Place mixture in bread pan and bake for specified time by your bread machine, approximately 4 hours and 10 minutes.

title: stir-fry
directions: Heat wok.
Add oil.
Add meat strips.
Cook very fast over high heat approximately 2 minutes.
Remove meat; set aside.
Let wok heat up.
Add all veggies; turn frequently for approximately 3 minutes.
Add meat, soy sauce and broth.
Cover for approximately 2 minutes.
Serve over bed of rice.
Serves approximately 8.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add bananas and eggs.
Beat. Stir in flour, salt, soda and vanilla.
Stir to blend, but do not overmix.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: marinated turkey
directions: Put turkey in a plastic container.
Make enough brine so the turkey can be covered.
Put the turkey in the refrigerator for 1 or 2 days to cure in the brine.
Put on hot covered grill in a foil pan.
Keep a little water in the bottom of the pan at all times while it is cooking.
It will take about 4 hours to grill your turkey.

title: date-nut muffins
directions: Grease a muffin pan.
In medium bowl, stir together dates, boiling water, corn oil and vanilla.
In smaller bowl, mix the two flours, sugar, walnuts and baking soda.
Add to date mixture. Stir until moistened.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: salmon-shrimp casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan;
stir	in flour.
Add soup and milk all at once.
Cook	and
stir
until mixture thickens and bubbles. Remove from heat; add cheese, stirring until melted. Gently stir in shrimp,	salmon and peas.
Turn into casserole. Bake, uncovered, stirring frequently,
for 40 to 45 minutes at 425°. Place baking powder
biscuits
on top.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and pour over cream mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
May sliver almond Hershey bars over the top.
Refrigerate until consumed.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs and vanilla. Measure and sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts; mix thoroughly with spoon.
Pour into tube pan and bake in a 300° oven until done, about 1 1/4 hours.

title: pop-a-pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place muffin halves on baking pan. Spread pizza sauce over each muffin half.
Place pepperoni slices on muffin halves.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
(Cheese can be placed, then pepperoni, if desired.)
Place in oven and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until cheese is bubbly.
Carefully remove from oven.
Decorate with remaining ingredients, if desired.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Form meat balls and brown in saucepan with chopped onions until golden brown.
Combine the tomatoes, water, tomato sauce, bay leaves and 2 tablespoons sugar and cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add meat balls to sauce.
Cook spaghetti and pour meat balls and sauce over them.
Serve.

title: oven barbecue round steak
directions: Cut steak in serving pieces; dredge in flour.
Brown in shortening.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Turn into casserole.
Mix together remaining ingredients. Pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 2 hours.
Check during cooking; add more water if necessary.
Serves 6.

title: brenda carnes' kentucky butter cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and extract.
Mix dry ingredients; add alternately with buttermilk.
Beat 3 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 12-cup tube pan.
Bake for 55 to 70 minutes in preheated 325° oven.
Top with Butter Sauce as soon as cake is done.

title: sweet rolls(sugar-free, low-fat)
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, water and oil.
Roll out in rectangular pattern.
Drizzle with honey, chopped nuts and cinnamon.
Roll up and slice in 1/2-inch sections.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Add all ingredients and mix. Refrigerate. This is best made the night before.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli up fine; peel parts of stalk and dice thin into salad.
Combine 1 cup Miracle Whip salad dressing (I use Hellmann's real mayonnaise) and 1/2 cup sugar and mix together. Pour over salad.
Let stand in refrigerator 4 hours before serving.

title: dipping mustard
directions: Combine the dry mustard and white vinegar and refrigerate overnight. Mix together the eggs and sugar and add to mustard and vinegar mixture. Cook in a double boiler until thick, or microwave on high, checking often and stirring until thick.

title: strawberry twinkie dessert
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan with Twinkies.
Mix pudding according to directions on box and pour over Twinkies.
Spoon strawberries over this and top with Cool Whip.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Cream butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy; stir in pecans.
Gradually stir in flour until well blended.
Cover; chill 1 hour or until firm enough to handle. Divide dough in 8 equal pieces.
On lightly floured board, roll each in 1/2-inch wide ropes.
Cut in 1 3/4-inch lengths; taper ends, then shape in crescents.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 300° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
While warm, roll in granulated sugar.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Put Doritoes in casserole dish, and tear chicken and put on top of chips.
Put one cup of chicken broth on top.
Put soup and cheese in sauce pan; melt cheese.
Saut onion and bell peppers in butter.
Mix cheese mixture and butter mixture together, with rotel tomatoes, and pour on top.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter milkshake
directions: In a stainless steel pan, bring 1 1/2 to 2 cups water to a boil.
Add 1 family sized tea bag or equivalent loose tea.
Turn off the heat and let this steep 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour tea into a 2-quart pitcher and add 3/4 cup sugar.
Add cold water to the tea bag and squeeze out into pitcher.
Fill pitcher with cold water. Now you're ready to add ice and enjoy a glass of tea!

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix ingredients (except vegetables).
Pour mixture over vegetables and marinate overnight.
Shake container occasionally to mix.

title: karo candy
directions: Bring to boil.
Take off stove.
Add 1 cup peanut butter.
Mix well and pour over cornflakes in large bowl.
Mix well and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and press down.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend Crisco and margarine until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually (while mixing) until dissolved. Add 1 whole egg at a time, mixing after each one, until all are added.
Continue mixing, adding dry ingredients and alternating with milk.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: old fashioned buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: mom's vegetable dish casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly all vegetables with celery soup.
Place in buttered casserole and cover with French fried onions.
Cook until bubbly.

title: easy turtle candies
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil, shiny side up; grease.
For each candy, place 3 pecan halves in a Y-shape on foil.
Place 1 caramel candy in center of each pecan Y. Bake just until candy is melted, 9 to 10 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill deep pie plate at least 2/3 full with apples.
Mix cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar and sprinkle over apples.
Cool the melted margarine and beat together with egg, 1 cup sugar and flour. Add the nuts and spread mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are cooked.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and place in casserole bowl.
Mix 1 cup corn flake crumbs and 1/4 cup margarine.
Pour over top of casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dirty rice and beans
directions: Brown sausage with onion and bell pepper.
Drain if necessary. Cook rice according to directions.
Mix with sausage mixture and serve with red beans.

title: sugar snap peas and peppers
directions: Cook garlic in olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add peas and peppers; cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: marinated london broil
directions: *Hellmann's Dijonnaise works well, too!

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix sugar and oil together. Add milk, yeast mixture and all of the dry ingredients. Store in refrigerator and make out as needed.

title: batter-up brownies
directions: Melt shortening in saucepan over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed. Mix thoroughly.
Spread in well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Boil spareribs 1 to 1 1/2 hours in water.
Drain.
Cut excess fat off.
Put in casserole dish, uncovered.
Pour enough barbecue sauce over ribs just enough to cover them.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 300°.

title: amazing fruit custard
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in blender.
Blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes, then add fruit.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: simple lemon bars
directions: Mix together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven about 20 to 25 minutes or until very light brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In large saucepan cook zucchini until crisp-tender, 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain well and set aside.
In same pan cook onions and green pepper in butter until tender, not brown.
Remove from heat. Stir in mushrooms, dry sauce mix, water and tomato paste, mix well.
Gently stir in zucchini and Mozzarella cheese.
Turn into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking pan or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lattice bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix in sugar, salt, butter, wheat germ and oats.
Stir in 2 cups flour or just enough to make dough leave sides of bowl.
Turn out on floured surface.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes until dough is smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turning to coat all sides.
Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk, about 2 hours.
Punch down.
Cut off 1/4 of dough.
Shape remaining dough and place in 8 or 9-inch spring-form or layer pan. Roll remaining dough in 1/4-inch ropes.
Arrange in lattice fashion on dough in pan.
Brush with egg wash.
Sprinkle with additional wheat germ and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately and cool on rack.

title: squash casserole
directions: Prepare squash; boil until tender and drain thoroughly.
Place squash in medium-sized mixing bowl.
Add onions, butter, soup, salt, pepper and 1/2 of the cheese.
Mix well and pour in casserole dish.
Add remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
(I stir all of the cheese into squash.)

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot shortening.
Add 1 cup water, bouillon cube and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Meanwhile, drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Add reserved pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thick and bubbly.

title: barbecued opossum
directions: Place the opossum in a baking pan lined with aluminum foil. Prepare the barbecue sauce by combining the remaining ingredients. Baste the animal with the sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours, basting frequently with sauce.
Uncover the meat and cook further until browned.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle on salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of flour on top.
Pour enough milk over potatoes to see milk in between, but do not cover.
Salt and pepper chops, then place them on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: squirrel stew
