directions: Cook squirrel until tender.
Add rest of ingredients; cook until potatoes are done, then add chili powder and sugar.
(Rabbit may be used instead of squirrel.)

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Put sugar and cinnamon in a plastic Ziploc bag.
Add biscuit pieces, a few at a time, and shake to coat.
Place all pieces in a greased tube pan.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Boil brown sugar and margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.
Let cool for 15 minutes. Remove from pan and serve upside down.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornflakes and place in a greased casserole dish.
Cover with crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: classic pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine ingredients in order.
Pour in pie shell and bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes, or until a knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in the bottom of a Bundt pan.
In a bowl, mix brown sugar and nuts.
Pour in pan.
In separate bowl, mix sugar and cinnamon.
Tear biscuits or break into fourths.
Roll in cinnamon sugar.
Lay in pan and pour remaining sugar mixture in. Melt other stick of butter and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
It's delicious with vanilla icing.

title: snicker pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into deep dish pie pan or onto graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: cranberry apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with fork.
Divide in half and roll out between 2 sheets of wax paper and put into 9-inch pie pan.
Set other ball of dough aside while preparing filling.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar by hand.
Add flour and soda to mixture. Add crushed pineapple and beat well.
Add nuts and beat well again.
Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan 40 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 350°.
Cool and refrigerate.
Powdered sugar frosting may be used when the cake is cool.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Remove and save 2 tablespoons of bacon grease. Brown beef and onions in grease.
Drain beans and combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: petie's (dog) treaties
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cut in butter until crumbly in food processor (with slicing blade).
Stir in egg.
Slowly add broth.
Put on floured surface and knead 5 minutes.
Divide in half and chill 1 hour.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 325° on cookie sheet 20 to 30 minutes until firm and dry to the touch.
Your dog will love them!

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all together and mix. Cool overnight.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill. Serve with various crackers of choice or even fresh vegetables.

title: brownies
directions: Put ingredients in a bowl in order listed, mixing well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
These are rich, cake-like brownies.

title: potato chip cookie mix
directions: Bake 350° for 30 minutes in 9x13 pan.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco, eggs and pumpkin together.
In separate bowl, sift flour and all dry ingredients.
Mix
all ingredients together with pumpkin mixture.
Mix well; add nuts and raisins. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Cut each chicken wing at joints to make 3 pieces; discard tips or save to use in making stock.
Place chicken in ungreased rectangular baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate, turning chicken occasionally, at least 1 hour.

title: potato salad-southern georgia style
directions: Boil and check texture of potatoes.
In a bowl, place 1 quart Kraft real mayonnaise and 2 heaping tablespoons French's yellow mustard.
Add all other ingredients except potatoes.
Layer dish with potatoes, then alternating other ingredients and potatoes in layers.

title: onion supper bread
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Prepare mix using package directions.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with onion.
Mix sour cream and cheese; spoon atop.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes; cut in squares.

title: poppy seed cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Pour into Bundt cake pan, greased with Crisco.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake pulls away from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pea-can salad
directions: Mix together and serve chilled.

title: frozen blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, baking powder and salt. In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in the dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in frozen blueberries.
Fill greased or paper lined muffin cups two thirds full.
Combined sugar and nutmeg; sprinkle over muffins.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add sugar, then liquid and butter.
Add egg and mix.
Stir in cranberries. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes a 9 x 4-inch loaf.

title: breakfast bake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan lay broken bread on bottom of pan.
Put sausage or bacon on top of bread.
Grate cheese and put on top of meat layer.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over other 3 layers.
Put mushrooms on top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned chocolate fudge
directions: Butter loaf pan, 9x5x3 inches.
Combine sugar, milk, chocolate, corn syrup, and salt in a 2 quart sauce pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and sugar is dissolved.
Cook, stirring occasionally, to 234 degrees on candy thermometer (or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball which flattens when removed from water).

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs (or egg whites) until light and add to shortening-sugar.
Mash bananas or press through sieve and add lemon juice.
Blend with creamed mixture.
Sift flour (unless presifted), baking powder and salt together and mix quickly into banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan in moderate oven (375°) about 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 1 (1 pound) loaf.

title: quick and easy granola bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; set aside. Bring brown sugar and syrup to a boil in a small saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla until blended.
Pour peanut butter mixture over cereal mixture, stirring until coated; let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Press mixture into 13 X 9 inch pan; cool in pan on a wire rack.
Cut into bars.

title: waldorf astoria stew
directions: Double soup, water, tapioca and sugar.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients.
Add next 5 and beat again. Fold in last 4 into the batter.
Place into 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve with party crackers.

title: champagne frozen salad
directions: Cream your cheese and sugar well; then add all the ingredients but Cool Whip.
At the end, fold in Cool Whip.
Put in cupcake holders and freeze.
Remove 30 minutes before serving.
Stays frozen a long time.

title: pork chops in beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and lay pork chops on top of beans.
Bake for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: molded harvard beet salad
directions: Add onion and horseradish to dissolved jello.
Fold in beets and celery.
Pour in mold and chill until set.
Serve with sour cream.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Top with mixture of the melted margarine and crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: onion rings
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Beat pancake mix, egg, oil and bouillon cube together.
Dip onion rings into mixture.
Drain and fry in 1 inch of cooking oil.

title: fritters
directions: Mix together and drop by spoonfuls into deep fryer.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Gradually add water, blending until smooth.
Cook over high heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Reduce heat and continue cooking until clear, 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Blend in slightly beaten egg yolk to which a little of the hot mixture has been added.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon rind, lemon juice and butter.

title: easter salad
directions: Dissolve
jello
in water; add pineapple and cool.
Stir in softened
cream
cheese
and nuts.
Whip the cream and fold into mixture.
Pour into oblong baking dish.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares
and serve on lettuce leaf as salad or in sherbet dishes for dessert.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and water in pan.
Add boiling water and cook stirring until clear and thickened.
Cool completely.
Beat egg whites at high speed till foamy.
Slowly add sugar and beat until stiff but not dry.
Turn speed to low and add salt and vanilla.
Gradually add cornstarch mixture, and mix with mixer. Beat at high speed and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cuts well and never gets sticky.

title: lemon custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs (yolks) and butter; add cornstarch, salt, milk, lemon juice and rind.
Cook over moderate heat until thick. Cook pie crust lightly.
Pour mix in crust.
Beat 6 egg whites until stiff and 1 tablespoon sugar for each egg white and 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Beat until holds a peak.
Add to top of pie.
Bake at 300° until lightly browned.
Makes 2 pies.

title: dip for fresh fruits
directions: Combine and use as dip for fresh fruits (especially good with strawberries).

title: swiss steak
directions: Put flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag, add steak and shake up until coated with flour mixture. Heat oil in large skillet.
Brown coated steak in hot oil.
Place sliced onion on top of meat, pour tomatoes over the top and simmer over low heat until onions and meat are tender. If gravy gets too thick, add a little hot water as needed.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Dice the beef and green onion into small pieces. Blend into the softened cream cheese.
Add the diced black olives if desired. These will add mildness by cutting the onion flavor.
Wrap to prevent the onion aroma from taking over your refrigerator.
If possible allow the ball to set overnight for the flavors to marry. The beef has a pretty high sodium content, so it can be rinsed under water to reduce the sodium content.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: polar bear pie
directions: Mix apple, egg, flour, sugar, baking powder and pecans well by hand.
Pour into 1 (8-inch) round cake pan (well-greased).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Fill with vanilla ice cream. Top with broken toffee pieces.
Drizzle with chocolate sauce and whipped cream.

title: mom l's bisque tortoni(italian frozen dessert)
directions: Whip cream and sugar until stiff; set aside.
Dissolve coffee in rum in small cup.
Fold rum mixture into whipped cream with spatula.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture. Spoon into fluted cups and place in freezer after garnishing with nuts and cherries. Serve frozen.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Pack firmly into an ungreased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked salmon cakes
directions: Using the butter, saute onions and celery.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 8 patties.
Roll in flour. Bake on greased cookie sheet 35 to 45 minutes.
Turn once.
Bake in 375° oven.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender, then drain and mash.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise, onion, eggs, salt and pepper together and combine with squash.
Place in buttered casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs, grated cheese and 1/2 stick butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 40 minutes.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Beat in sugar.
Add flour alternately with the liquids.

title: 9 layer chili dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, yogurt, cream cheese and taco mix. Divide 2/3 and 1/3. Spread beans on the bottom of a 9x13 pan and layer as follows onto the beans: chili; cream cheese mixture; salsa; 1 1/2 cups lettuce; chiles; diced tomatoes; shredded cheese; 1 1/2 cups lettuce.

title: deep dish crazy crust pizza
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and season with oregano, basil and garlic salt.
Pour into greased, deep dish pizza pan. Brown hamburger, onion and Italian seasonings.
Spoon hamburger on top of batter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove pie dough from oven.
Spread pizza sauce and cheeses on top.
Bake until cheeses melt, approximately 10 minutes.

title: vegetable loaf
directions: Boil vegetables 10 minutes; drain.
Grease 8 x 8-inch pan; put layer of corn flake crumbs on bottom of pan.
Mash and mix all other ingredients.
Put on corn flakes; top with thick layer of corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting into squares.
Good with chicken or beef.

title: monkey pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Add onion, cooking until onions are clear. Drain beef fat off and add corn or peas. Lightly oil casserole dish or spray with nonstick cooking spray. Spoon the mixture in casserole dish; pat the mixture flat. Spread mashed potatoes over the top of the mixture. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° in oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Calories: 161; cholesterol 26 mg; total fat 7 g and sodium 365 mg.

title: savory cheese spread "but of course"
directions: Blend all ingredients using a wire whisk at medium speed. Cover and chill until serving time.
Serve as a spread with crackers.

title: deep dish brownie surprise
directions: Cool crumbled brownie in deep dish pan.
Pour chilled pudding over brownie.
Spread Cool Whip.
Sprinkle Butterfinger crumbs all over.
Chill to set.

title: skeeter's banana ice cream pie
directions: Slice bananas on cooled pie crust (use Skeeter's Pie Crust recipe).
Combine milk and pudding; mix well.
Beat in vanilla ice cream.
Pour over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle pecans on top or just leave plain.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: marshmallow pudding
directions: Pour cream over marshmallows.
Let stand 2 hours.
Add 1 can crushed pineapple, 2 bananas and 2 oranges.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Place oil in Dutch oven.
Heat until hot; add flour and stir continually until browned.
This is your roux.
Add other ingredients in order.
Cook until done.
Add water if it cooks down a little low.
Serve with rice.
Add some crab meat if desired.

title: corn succotash
directions: Makes 4 servings.
This is also good made with canned or frozen vegetables.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach.
Add cream cheese and butter to spinach and stir until melted.
Top spinach mixture with stuffing and margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix in saucepan and cook over low heat until forms ball. Cool.
Knead into desired shapes.
Let harden.
Store unused dough in plastic bag.

title: 1-2-3 brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients in order.
Beat well.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan, 12 pieces.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool; cut.
If double, use 9 x 13-inch and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Can freeze.

title: no peek chicken
directions: In a small roaster, sprayed with Pam, put in chicken and mushroom soup.
Mix well rice and water.
Put in bottom of roaster.
Remove skim from chicken thighs or drumsticks, then put chicken pieces on top of rice mixture in the roaster.

title: apple peanut butter crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12 x 7 x 2-inch metal baking pan.
In small bowl, stir together the flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in peanut butter and butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Slice apples into greased baking pan.
Sprinkle peanut butter mixture over apples.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Top with ice cream, frozen yogurt or whipped topping.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rhubarb cheesecake dessert
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and salt, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Press into a greased 13 X 9 X 2 inch baking dish.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla;
mix well.
Pour over the crust.
Bake for 20 - 25 minutes or until center is set and edges are light brown.
Cool. In a saucepan, combine the rhubarb, sugar, water, cornstarch and cinnamon, bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Stir in food coloring if desired.
Remove from the heat, cool.
Pour over filling.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saut onion, bell pepper and celery in butter.
Add soup, tomatoes, mushrooms, cheese and chicken in a large pot.
Simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook spaghetti in the leftover chicken broth.
Combine spaghetti and sauce.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: banana bread
directions: In large bowl combine 1 c. flour, sugar, baking powder and soda, and salt.
Add bananas, margarine, and milk; beat until blended on low, then on high 2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining flour, mix well.

title: ruth's french dressing
directions: Shake well and let stand in refrigerator to blend, then strain.
(I prefer to leave onion, etc. in.)
This makes about a quart, and keeps well in the fridge.
Enjoy.

title: microwave acorn squash 'n apples
directions: Pierce
whole
squash
and place in oven.
Microwave on High 10
to
minutes or until soft to touch.
Let stand 5 minutes. Cut
in
half; remove seeds.
Place cut side up in 2 quart
baking dish.
Fill centers of squash with apples.
Top each with
2 tablespoons brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter and dash of cinnamon. Cover with plastic wrap and continue baking 6 to
minutes
or until apples are tender.
Let stand, covered, 2 to 3 minutes before serving.
Serves four.

title: deborah's sweet & sour chicken
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; stir in vinegar, juice from pineapple, soy sauce, salt, garlic, paprika, ginger, celery and onion.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, stirring constantly until thickened.

title: orange date nut fruit cake
directions: Chop nuts; cut dates into small pieces.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of flour.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift the rest of flour (3 1/2 cups) with soda. Add flour and buttermilk alternately to butter and egg mixture. Stir in grated orange rind.
Add dates and nuts.
Pour into tube cake pan lined with wax paper.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Remove from pan.
Remove paper.
Return cake to pan and drizzle with topping.

title: chocolate almond pie
directions: Melt chocolate bars in	double	boiler	with
milk; add marshmallows and continue to
heat until melted and thoroughly mixed.
Cool.
Fold in Cool
Whip
and
pour
into	pie shell. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: paper bag baked turkey
directions: Mix pepper, salt, paprika, hot water and peanut oil and let set 10 minutes.

title: red bean pie
directions: Combine ingredients and place in uncooked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Make a meringue with reserved egg white; spread on pie and brown in oven.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, milk, butter, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Mix with electric mixer.
Add cinnamon.
Pour into an 8-inch baking dish; add topping.

title: kromer family birthday cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Cream yolks.
Add sugar.
Gradually add cold water.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt, then vanilla. Beat egg whites; fold into batter.
Line bottom of two 10-inch round cake pans with brown paper.
Divide batter between layers. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Slice each layer in half to make 4 layers.
Frost with Chocolate Butter Frosting and cover with shaved nuts (pecans are best). Refrigerate.

title: shrimp bake
directions: Saute chopped vegetables in oil.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Add shrimp, rice and seasoning.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: garden salad with almonds and oranges
directions: Wash and tear lettuce into bite-size pieces (refrigerate). Combine almonds and 1/4 cup sugar in saucepan, stirring over medium heat until sugar browns.
Cool caramelized almonds on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Break into tiny pieces and set aside.

title: holiday traveler snack mix
directions: Spread coconut evenly on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly toasted, stirring after 5 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool.
Combine toasted coconut, peanuts, chocolate pieces and cereal, tossing gently.
Store snack mix in an airtight container.
Yield: 10 1/2 cups.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Heat butter, flour, salt and pepper. Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Cook on low heat until mixture thickens.
Spread 1 pie crust over bottom of a 3-quart baking dish.
Add chicken mixture.
Cover with remaining pie crust.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Beat sugar and oleo, then add eggs.
Beat until mixed well; add flour and blend.
Add cocoa and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased and floured large cookie sheet at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: breakfast creek meat loaf
directions: Chop up your onion, pepper and bread together in a food processor.
Add to meat and egg.
Mix lightly and add remaining ingredients (get both hands in there).
Shape into a loaf or a round baking pan rubbed lightly with Crisco.
Brush top of loaf with additional catsup and add strips of bacon for a nice country flavor.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: cream cheese peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well the cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Gently fold in whipped topping.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours.
Thaw 10 minutes before serving. Drizzle with hot fudge topping.

title: wild rice, chicken and artichoke salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Let cool.
In large bowl, combine rice, chopped artichokes (reserve marinade), toasted almonds, green onions, green pepper and chicken.
Mix reserved marinade with 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Add to salad; let stand overnight.
Add pepper to taste.

title: memere's sponge candy
directions: Combine sugar and Karo syrup in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Bring to a hard crack stage (305°) and remove from heat. Quickly stir in baking soda. Mix well (volume will triple in size).
Pour into a lightly buttered shallow 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: breakfast taco
directions: Scramble eggs in skillet. Lay tortillas flat and spoon eggs over the 4 tortillas. Sprinkle with ham and cheese. Roll up to enclose filling. Place tacos in a microwave-safe dish. Microwave for 30 seconds or until cheese is melted. Serve immediately.

title: make ahead enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onions with meat until meat is cooked.
Add all ingredients except tortillas and cheese.
Layer tortillas and meat mixture, beginning and ending with meat mixture.
Cover with cheese and freeze now, or bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon gingerbread cake(low-fat)
directions: Cream sugar and margarine at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy (about 5 minutes).
Add lemon rind and egg white; beat at medium speed until well blended.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Open and drain cans of fruit in a large bowl cut peaches into cubes, slice bananas, and cubed apples.
Add all canned fruit and marshmallow cream.
Mix together gently.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot and cold water, pineapple and juice and nuts.
Stir and chill until thick and firm.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip with mixer until thick.
Spread until thick.

title: swedish meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, egg, stuffing (cornflakes), nutmeg and 1/3 can of soup.
Shape into loaf.
Place in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian cookies
directions: Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Mix flour, baking powder and sugar with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cut Crisco into flour mixture. Make well in center and add milk, eggs and anise extract.
Mix well with hands.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add beans and Ro-Tel.
Cook a few minutes, then add Cheddar cheese soup.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Place shells in large baking dish.
Add some of the hamburger mixture.
Top with cheese slices.
Add shells, hamburger mixture and cheese slices.
When you are through layering casserole, pour enchilada sauce over it and grated cheese to top it all.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together in a blender, except coconut on top.
Bake for 40 minutes, until knife comes out clean.

title: butter cookies(sviesto sausainiai)
directions: Cream butter and cheese; sift in flour.
Mix and chill overnight.
Roll thin; cut into squares.
Fill squares with pureed stewed apricots, prunes or jam.
Bake in 450° oven until lightly browned.
Remove from pan; sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: grandad's piccalilli
directions: Slice tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Place in layers in a large enamel kettle and sprinkle salt between each layer.
Cover and let stand for 24 hours.
Drain and rinse twice.
Tie pickling spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Mix sugar, vinegar and pickling spices and bring to a boil.
Add vegetables and bring to a rolling boil and cook for 10 minutes.
Pack in jars; seal and process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Let stand for 2 weeks before using.
Yields 15 to 17 pints.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: In a two-quart casserole dish, place the broccoli and drained slices of water chestnuts (cut thin).
Cover with soup.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and butter.
Sprinkle on top of soup and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: layered salad
directions: Cook
macaroni	shells following package directions and drain well
in
a colander.
Cool to room temperature.
Place lettuce in	an
even
layer in the bottom of a 3 quart, clear glass
bowl. Works
best
if
it has straight sides.
Arrange carrots in an even layer over the lettuce.
Cover with a layer of macaroni, then the tomatoes, peas, onion and ham.	Sprinkle top
with
cheese. Combine
the
mayonnaise and Ranch powder. Mound
the
dressing in the center of the salad.
Arrange the egg
wedges
around the dressing.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill.

title: gooey pull-apart
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan (can use Pam or Baker's Joy). Put rolls (frozen) in Bundt pan. Sprinkle ingredients over rolls. Drizzle melted butter over rolls. Let sit overnight on counter. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strip pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Cut cucumbers into strips and cover with boiling water and let set until hot.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes and pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: brew-ha-ha punch
directions: Stir together sugar and 2 quarts water until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: squash supreme
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Mash and add sour cream, soup, carrot, onion, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle a layer of crumbs in a shallow casserole dish.
Spoon squash mixture over crumbs.
Cover with additional crumbs and dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pink arctic freeze(delicious!)
directions: Mix in order given and freeze in metal or plastic loaf pan overnight.
Slice off and serve on lettuce leaf.
Delicious!

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper; drain.
Mix beef, corn and tomatoes.
Pour into well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix cornmeal, egg and water to mix.
Pour this crust over mixture. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 9 people.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, make layers of cherry pie filling, pineapple, cake mix (dry), margarine and pecans.
Do Not Stir. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a springboard cake pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 2 hours in pan.
Top with choice (cherries, blueberries).

title: treat-to-eat cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar and pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes; sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: big boone's chili
directions: Puree
tomatoes
in a blender.	Pour water and tomatoes into a 1 1/2 or 2-gallon kettle and begin cooking over medium heat. Brown
beef
and onions in shortening; add to tomatoes. Add garlic, bay leaves, oregano, cumin, salt, chili powder and pepper. Bring
to a boil and reduce heat to simmer.
Simmer 2 1/3 to 3 hours.
Add
water if it gets too thick during cooking.
Add coriander
minutes
before chili is ready.
Mix flour with cold
water or tomato juice to form a paste and add to chili
near the
end
of cooking time in order to thicken; stir thoroughly. Best
made	at
least
1 day before serving. Serves 16 (8-ounce) servings.

title: 24-hour layer salad
directions: Place lettuce in a large clear glass bowl.
In the following order, layer: mushrooms, broccoli, carrots, eggs, onions and bacon on top.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese on top of bacon.
Mix sour cream, Miracle Whip, lemon juice, garlic and Parmesan cheese together with a wire whisk.
Spread over the top of salad, sealing the dressing to edges of the bowl.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese and the chives.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: hawaiian style chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Bone and skin chicken.
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch strips.
Toss with flour, salt and paprika. Cook chicken in 3 tablespoons heated oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until browned and tender (about 10 minutes).

Add remaining tablespoon oil, vegetables and drained pineapple chunks. Stir-fry until tender yet crisp, or about 3 to 4 minutes longer. Combine vinegar, soy sauce, 3/4 cup pineapple syrup and cornstarch.
Stir into contents of pan.
Bring to a boil and cook just until dressing clears and thickens.
Serve on bed of steamed rice.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven until set.
Make meringue with 3 egg whites; beat until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

title: minted confetti cole slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine green and red cabbages, carrots, green onions and mint.
In a separate bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour dressing over vegetables and toss until coated.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease shallow 2-quart dish.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Return beef to skillet and add taco seasoning, tomatoes and corn.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture into dish.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients (except sugar).
Blend margarine, sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and beat well with a spoon.
Gradually add to dry ingredients.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda, baking powder, salt, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Beat at medium speed until well mixed. Stir in zucchini, raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
(You may add 1/2 cup crushed nuts on top before you put it into oven.)

title: hamburger-pepper skillet
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add salt, peppers, onion, rice, water and sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Add Ro-Tel and tomatoes.
Heat for 5 minutes, then serve.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Add to wet mixture; drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and smash down with tongs of fork.
You may add nuts or sugar to top, or change flavor.
Almond is very good.
Makes about 4 dozen.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: hayden's hot hors d'oeuvre(microwave)
directions: Spread cream cheese in microwavable shallow dish.
Add chili and top with grated cheese.
Microwave on High until cheese melts. Serve with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch for 3 minutes.
Remove from stove and add orange juice and lemon juice to taste.
Pour over carrots.
Bake at 325° until thoroughly heated.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Add oleo and let stand 20 minutes.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: elite hash brown potatoes
directions: Combine these ingredients well and put in 9 x 13-inch cake dish.
Top with 1/2 cup crushed (finely) potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Combine and cook until onions are done.
Put over partly cooked sausages in covered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. This can be done a day before and reheated.
Use only 1/2 on 1 pound of sausages.
Store remainder in refrigerator.
Also excellent on pork chops.

title: hamburger fingers
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together in a bowl.
Spread on split roll, such as hot dog, hamburg or English muffin.
Broil for 5 to 6 minutes, or bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: cheesy corn bake
directions: Mix and pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and return to oven until melted.

title: mexican pork chili
directions: Brown pork chops.
Cook until all water is out of pan.
Add Pace picante sauce.
Cook on low heat until thickened to desired consistency.
Enjoy.

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and put half of them in a 9 x 13-inch pan or flower pot.
Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth with mixer. Mix in powdered sugar; fold in Cool Whip.
In separate bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Fold in cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture together.
Pour into pan or flower pot on cookie crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining cookie crumbs on top.
Chill or freeze.
May be served chilled or frozen.
In flower pot, may add flowers for decoration.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground beef and Italian sausage together.
Cook pasta in salt water with a small touch of butter until tender.
When meat is browned, drain off grease and set meat aside.
You can saute your onion and bell pepper if you wish.
It will be more tender if you do.
After vegetables get tender, remove from skillet and set aside in a small bowl.
Return meat to skillet and add spaghetti sauce and water.
Heat until bubbling.
Now put pasta in large baking dish.
Spread onion and pepper over pasta.
Then top with mushrooms, pepperoni, ham and the meat sauce.
Put in oven and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Then remove from oven and cover top with Mozzarella cheese.
Put back in oven and cook until cheese bubbles and starts to brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Crumble 1 pack of Town House crackers and spread over bottom of pan.
Mix the soup and broth and pour half of this mixture over cracker crumbs.
Layer diced chicken on top.
Pour other half of mixture over chicken.
Salt and pepper.
Crumble another pack of crackers on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: basic chicken stock
directions: Place all ingredients in the cold water.
Bring to a boil. Skim off foam.
Simmer slowly for 4 hours to reduce by one-third. Strain and freeze.

title: english rolled wafers
directions: Heat molasses to boiling point. Add oleo, then slowly, stirring constantly, add flour sifted with ginger and sugar. Drop small portions on greased inverted cookie pan 2-inches apart. Bake 15 minutes at 300°. Cool slightly. Remove from pan and roll over handle of wooden spoon. If they get too hard, put in oven for a second. Nuts may be added if desired.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk into
saucepan and cook to the soft ball stage (234°). Remove from heat.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Mix and boil 4 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Beat and add 1 cup chopped pecans.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In a large saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, unbeaten eggs, mashed bananas, then flour, sifted with soda and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a loaf pan.
Leave for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and tomato soup.
Set aside to cool, but not to set.
Combine diced green pepper, celery, hard-cooked egg, softened cream cheese, salad dressing and crab meat or tuna with Jell-O mixture.
Pour into mold.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Serve on lettuce with rolls or crackers (fancy).
May be served with a little dressing.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: squash casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in respective order.
Bake at 400° until boiling, then lower to 350° or 325° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry-pineapple mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mix in partially defrosted strawberries, pineapple and salt.
Pour half of the gelatin into an 8-cup mold and refrigerate until firm.
Keep remaining gelatin at room temperature.

title: country chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken pieces in salted water, just enough to cover, until done (50 to 60 minutes). Remove from water. Skin and debone meat.
Set aside.
To stock left in pot, add 3 tablespoons margarine, milk, salt, pepper and food coloring.
Heat.
Make biscuits with flour, 1 1/2 sticks margarine and milk.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out half of it thinly on floured board. Cut into long strips. Into boiling pot, drop dumplings, one at a time. When all are in, reduce heat to simmer and simmer 20 minutes without lid.
With slotted spoon, remove dumplings to greased 3-quart Pyrex dish. Top with chicken. Cover with as much of stock mixture as needed to make a juicy pie.
Roll out remaining dough. Cut into biscuits and put on top of pie.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: oyster cheese ball
directions: Mix together and make into a ball.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: general grant's cucumbers
directions: Peel and thinly slice cucumbers and onions.
Mix together vinegar and milk; pour over cucumber mix.
Add sugar.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill overnight.

title: garlic bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread on bread of your choice.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Mixture stores well in covered bowl in refrigerator.

title: party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt margarine in a large shallow baking dish.
Mix in Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Add cereals, peanuts and pretzels and mix thoroughly. Bake in oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Nuts can be added and/or put on top for decoration.

title: overnight seafood and macaroni casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with cover, combine all ingredients except peas and carrots; mix well.
Cover dish and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes.
Stir in peas and carrots.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer, or until set.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and oil.
Add sugar and vanilla and beat until thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, nuts and currants (or raisins).
Stir into the zucchini mixture.
Add pineapple and mix well.
Bake in 2 (5 x 9-inch) loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix cheese and crab together.
Form into a ball.
Cover with cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers, any type you like (Triscuits, etc.).

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread mix by package directions.
Add 1/2 of the cream style corn, 1/2 ground beef and 1/2 of the grated cheese.

title: banana split cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Layer as follows.

title: roasted emu
directions: Shake one tablespoon flour in a turkey sized roasting bag. Pour off excess flour.
In a large roasting pan, place the steaks side by side inside the bag.
Do not layer meat.
Sprinkle lemon pepper, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce onto steaks.
Add beef broth to bottom of bag, ensuring that all meat is kept in liquid.
Sprinkle onion on top.
Close bag with tie and make six 1-inch slits in top of bag.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: granny's supper
directions: Arrange evenly in greased 2 quart baking dish, potato slices and 1 tablespoon onion.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Mix ground beef with milk, cracker crumbs, catsup, onion, salt and pepper.
Spread mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix the beans, sour cream, taco seasoning and mayonnaise together.
Then add green onions.
Also add black olives, tomatoes and Monterey Jack and Cheddar cheeses (amounts of cheeses are as desired).

title: top-stove beans and meat balls
directions: Cover and cook for a few minutes, until heated.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together and pour in tube pan.
Bake for 40 minutes in oven set at 350°.

title: date balls
directions: Cook dates, butter, yolks, sugar and vanilla in heavy iron skillet.
Stirring constantly, boil 5 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies and pecans.
Shape into bite-size pieces; roll into coconut.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients until dissolved.
Drain and add pineapple.
Keep juice from pineapple and add water to make 1 3/4 cups.
Stir in jello.
Add 4 medium apples, diced small.
Add the crushed pineapple and stir in jello.
Top with chopped nuts.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in lukewarm water.
Combine soda and buttermilk.
Mix flour and Crisco (cut).
Add yeast and buttermilk mixture.
Refrigerate 2 hours (overnight).
Roll out and cut. Brush tops with warm butter.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 375°.

title: chili bean salad
directions: Layer: chili beans, stewed tomatoes, onion, lettuce and cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Then add dressing and top with cheese.

title: fr. bob's pea soup
directions: Soak the peas overnight after rinsing.
Put the peas in a large stockpot along with all the other ingredients and bring to a boil; cover and then simmer for 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Pour soup through a strainer and may be thinned with milk or water if necessary.
Serve hot with croutons or saltines.
Great in the winter months in Cleveland Heights!

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream together 1/2 cup peanut butter and butter; add sugar gradually and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix in flour sifted with salt.
Spread dough on ungreased cookie sheet (about 14 x 17-inch).
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Pour in greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: apricot bread
directions: Wash apricots, cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes, then drain, saving liquid.
Chop apricots very fine and set aside.
Add salt and baking soda to sifted flour and sift again.
Cream butter and sugar; stir in beaten egg.
Alternate, adding flour mixture to sugar mixture with milk and apricot liquid. Fold in chopped apricots.
Bake in preheated 350° oven in a wax paper lined loaf pan about 50 minutes.
Will make 1 large loaf or 2 medium loaves.
Test with toothpick in center to be sure it is well done before removing from oven.

title: mexican rice
directions: Heat skillet over medium high heat.
When skillet gets hot, add oil.
Add garlic; stir and quickly add rice.
Let sizzle for a spell.
Shake pan and stir to mix as rice glazes and some begins to turn a golden color.
Do not let burn!
Stir in onion.
Heat to boil the water and bouillon in microwave.
When onion is glazed and a portion of rice has turned golden, add hot chicken broth, chili powder, salsa picante, tomato sauce, peas, corn and carrots. Turn heat to low; cook for 2 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.
Cover again; let ingredients get well acquainted until all water is absorbed.

title: the best chocolate chip cookie
directions: Cream butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oats, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add chips, candy and nuts.
Roll into balls.
Bake 6 minutes at 375°.

title: frosty creme de menthe
directions: In blender container or food processor bowl with metal blade, combine all ingredients, except mints.
Blend on high speed 1 minute or until smooth.
Serve in champagne glasses.
Top each with mint triangle.
Yields 10 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: fluffy butter icing
directions: Mix flour with milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add to thick mixture and heat for 10 minutes or until as fluffy as desired.
Icing becomes harder when refrigerated.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well.
Makes enough for six 2 pound chickens.

title: orange dessert
directions: Set Eagle Brand milk in refrigerator overnight.
Put in mixer bowl and
beat
4 minutes.	Fold in Cool Whip and frozen orange juice.
Fold
in Mandarin oranges.	Mix crackers, sugar and oleo together.
Save 3/4 cup for topping.
Pat crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour orange mixture in and sprinkle rest of crackers on top. Refrigerate.

title: old fashioned fried pies(apple or apricot)
directions: Roll out individual biscuit to thin saucer size.
Add tablespoon of fruit in center.
Fold dough into 1/2 size.
Crimp edges.
Place on butter Crisco skillet and brown on each side. Delicious.

title: strawberry-nut-sour cream salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine Jell-O with boiling water, stirring until dissolved.
Add strawberries, bananas, pineapple and nuts. Put half mixture in shallow dish and refrigerate for 1 1/2 hours. Then spread sour cream over top gently and spoon balance of mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: bread sticks
directions: Cut hot dog buns into lengthwise strips.
Melt the butter and brush each stick with it.
Sprinkle the sticks with onion or garlic salt and poppy, celery or caraway seed.
Bake at 225° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: tangy fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit thoroughly, reserving 2 1/2 cups of juice. Combine puddings and fruit juice and bring to boil.
Chill. (This thickens as it cools.)
Fold in pineapple, oranges and half bottle of maraschino cherries.
Just before serving, add 2 bananas, sliced.

title: pistachio inside-outside cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large mixer bowl, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Split into 3 layers.
Spread 1 cup frosting between layers and spoon rest into center and chill.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: First bring water to a boil; add oatmeal.
Stir and let stand 20 minutes.
Then cream sugars and salad oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to oatmeal mixture.
Then add oatmeal and vanilla and beat well.

title: jim's shanghai beef
directions: Saute beef in oil in a large skillet until browned (about 5 minutes).
Add cornstarch and blend well.
Add broth, water chestnuts, red peppers, scallions, soy sauce and black pepper. Bring to a full boil.
Stir frequently to keep from sticking. Stir in Minute rice and cover.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
Make 4 large or 6 small servings.

title: french apple squares
directions: Mix together with pastry blender or 2 knives the first 4 ingredients.
Blend in slightly beaten egg yolk and 2/3 cup milk (careful with milk, it may not need that much) to make a ball of soft dough, not wet, just right for rolling out.

title: fudge(quick and good)
directions: Simmer the first 3 ingredients.
Add the chocolate and boil 4 minutes.
Add the 1/2 jar marshmallow.
Stir and mix good.
Pour in pan.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and toss to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time, at least 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: jimmy carter dessert
directions: Layer 1:
Mix the nuts, flour and oleo. Blend and press in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender or cook in slow cooker.
In a large bowl, debone chicken; add can of cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and 3 cups of chicken broth.
Mix all these ingredients together.
Put in a large casserole dish.
Mix flour, milk and melted butter together, then pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: double coconut pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with prepared pastry. Stir together eggs, sugar, melted butter, lemon juice and vanilla. Stir in the coconut (mixture will be thick). Spoon coconut mixture into pastry-lined pie plate. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until pie is set and top is golden. Makes 10 servings.

title: sweet potato souffl
directions: Beat together and place in long baking dish. Add topping. Can add marshmallows to top.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute onions, beef and peppers; add salt and pepper.
Mix in tomato paste, tomato sauce and pizza sauce.
Stir and simmer 1/2 hour.
Add mushrooms and pepperoni.
Layer in dish, cooked macaroni, sauce and cheese.
Put most of cheese in middle layer. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Heat in oven long enough to heat good.

title: great depression cake
directions: In a large saucepan, simmer the first 5 ingredients for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend together the remaining ingredients and stir into mixture.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: fluffy jello salad
directions: *The liquid in the pineapple will make the other cup of liquid for the jello.

title: hearty dried beef chowder
directions: Pour water on potatoes; let stand 10 minutes.
Melt margarine in large pan.
Add flour, then stir in milk gradually.
Drain potatoes; rinse.
Stir potatoes, corn (with liquid), dried beef, salt, lemon pepper and celery salt into milk mixture.
Heat until hot.

title: 7 layer candy
directions: Melt oleo in a loaf cake pan.
Add graham crackers.
Sprinkle on coconut, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Cover with can of Eagle Brand milk.
Sprinkle on chopped nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remember to add each ingredient in order, and don't stir.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Chop onion, bell pepper and celery. Drain green beans, English peas and corn. Boil oil, vinegar and sugar 5 minutes; cool. Pour over vegetables and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: rice and peppers
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Put the oil in a frying pan and saute peppers and onions until soft, but not brown.
Stir in all the spices and raisins, then mix with rice.
Put in a covered casserole and bake 30-45 minutes, or until hot through. This dish is better if prepared the day before.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel avocado, mash.
Peel tomato and mince.
Mince onion.
Mix all ingredients with a fork.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hurry-up yeast rolls
directions: Preheat oven at 400°.
Measure water in a mixing bowl. Sprinkle in yeast and stir until dissolved.
Stir in biscuit mix. Beat vigorously.
Turn dough onto surface until well dusted with biscuit mix.
Knead until smooth, about 20 times.
Shape as desired, crescents, rolls, etc.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Cover with damp cloth.
Let rise in a warm place, free from draft, about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, depending on size.
Brush with butter or margarine after baking. Makes 12 to 16 rolls.

title: texas cornbread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, salt, baking powder and sugar; blend well.
In a separate bowl, combine eggs, oil and milk.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix just until moistened. Stir in corn and chilies; beat 1/2 minute.
Turn into greased 8 to 9-inch square pan.
(I use a cookie sheet, as we like thin cornbread.)
Bake in a preheated 400° oven until done, about 25 minutes.
Turn out on cooling rack.
Cut into squares and serve warm.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: orville's ho-made ice cream
directions: Slowly mix half and half to the Eagle Brand by adding a little half and half to the Eagle Brand until you have added one quart of the half and half.
Now add the vanilla and sugar.
Mix for 5 minutes.
Add second quart of half and half and stir again. Put in ice cream freezer and mix until ice cream freezer slows down.

title: tony's eggplant parmesan
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in oil until glistening.
Add tomatoes and juice.
Add seasonings.
Let sauce simmer until tomatoes cook-up and juice is cooked out.

title: spoon bread or corn pudding
directions: Stir all ingredients together and pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: creole burgers
directions: Saute ground beef and onions.
Stir in soup, ketchup and mustard.
Season with pepper.
Spoon into bottom half of buns and top with a slice of American cheese.
Place under broiler or in microwave to melt cheese.
Top with top half of bun.

title: pigs in blanket
directions: Slit each hot dog and place cheese inside.
Wrap crescent roll around each.
Hold together with toothpick.
Place in oven according to directions on package of rolls.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and eggs together.
Put into medium size casserole dish.
Add corn and milk to the first mixture.
Dot top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: kristen's cheesy hash browns
directions: Place potatoes in slow cooker.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Mix well.
Cover and cook on low 4-5 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples until soft; press through sieve.
Combine all ingredients in a pan.
Put, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 3 hours, stirring every hour.
Ladle into jars and seal.

title: cranberry orange crescents
directions: Unroll dough; separate into 8 triangles.
Combine remaining ingredients; spread evenly over each triangle.
Roll, place and bake crescents as directed on package label.

title: broccoli-stuffing bake
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed; add cooked (crisp-tender) broccoli, soup and cheese.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° until hot and cheese melts.
Double recipe; use 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Press in bottom of large casserole dish. Mix soup and milk; drizzle on top of beef. Layer Tater Tots on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until set in center.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Wash cranberries and grind; mix together with sugar and coconut.
Whip Dream Whip with milk as directed on package.
Fold into cranberry mixture.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water until tender, then drain. Combine carrots and butter in container of electric blender. Blend until smooth. Add remaining ingredients. Blend well. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 or 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Make sure it is done in the middle.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef until done.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Heat through.

In a small bowl, combine sour cream and cottage cheese. Layer the lasagna as follows in a large casserole dish: 1/3 meat mixture, 4 1/2 noodles (uncooked), 1/2 cottage cheese mixture, 4 ounces Mozzarella cheese, 1/2 the Parmesan cheese, 1/3 meat sauce, 4 1/2 noodles, rest of the cottage cheese mixture, rest of meat sauce, top with rest of Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese. Pour water on top of all.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 20 more minutes.
Then take out of oven and let sit for 20 minutes.
Serve.
Excellent!!

title: summer squash
directions: Slice squash thin.
If seeds are big, remove them.
Put butter in bottom of pan.
Add squash, salt, pepper and a small amount of water.
Cover and cook slowly until tender.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla.
Drop spoonful of dough onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove to rack to cool.

title: baked cabbage jambalaya
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole.
Cover and bake in a 275° oven for two hours, stirring halfway through cooking.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: jalapeno cranberry salsa
directions: Cut limes into 6 pieces each, including rind, chopped finely. Add cranberries and process very briefly in food processor.
Place in plastic container and add jalapenos, cilantro leaves and sugar. Mix well.
Chill 15 minutes up to overnight.
Serve as an appetizer with baked tortilla chips.
Serve over baked fish or chicken or as a relish.
Yields 6 servings.
Has 45 calories, fat free.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water or pineapple juice.
Stir in crushed pineapple.
Let mixture cool.
Stir in shredded cheese.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: sunburst orange pie
directions: *To make your own crumbs, crush about 16 graham crackers in a plastic bag with a rolling pin.

title: curried rice ham rolls
directions: In a skillet, saute onion in butter until tender about 3 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks and add to milk, then to dry ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until it boils.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Press 1/2 cup chopped pecans on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes only. (Do not overbake.)

title: mama's blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in pan in which you intend to bake cobbler.
Combine flour, baking powder, sugar, most of the melted margarine and enough of the milk to make the mixture like cake batter, approximately 1 cup or less.
Pour into pan with remaining melted margarine.

title: salad dressing to shake
directions: Shake well in jar and keep refrigerated.

title: ritzy fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash fish fillets, then dry them off with a paper towel to absorb some of the excess water.
Lay as many as you can close together in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish. Put a little dab of butter (1/2 teaspoon) on each fillet.
Pour a little lemon juice over all fillets.
(I use a squeeze bottle of lemon juice and just "squeeze" it all over.)
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Pull out pan and crumble Ritz crackers (1 to 2 rolls from package in a box) all over fillets.
Add shredded Mozzarella all over crackers.
Bake another 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Dip into seafood sauce as you eat, if desired.

title: ouie gooie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, eggs and margarine in mixer bowl.
Press, using your hand into greased baking pan.
Combine confectioners sugar, cream cheese and vanilla in mixer bowl until creamed and smooth.
You may have to add a little water to make it smooth.
Spread over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: no-crust pumpkin pie(low-fat)
directions: Spray a glass pie plate with nonstick cooking spray (Pam). Mix all ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve with lite Cool Whip, if desired.

title: german apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: slow-cooked ribs
directions: Heat oven to 200°. In a saucepan, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion and cook 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in garlic and cook 1 minute. Stir in water, vinegar, syrup, Worcestershire, mustard, chili powder, salt, pepper, ginger and tomato paste. Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture begins to thicken. Place ribs in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Pour sauce over ribs. Cover dish tightly with heavy foil and bake until tender, about 4 hours.

title: vanilla pudding ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Beat in sugar, pudding mix and milk until smooth.
Stir in half and half and coconut.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake the cake and prepare the pudding.
In a large bowl, layer 1/2 of the cake (crumbled).
Sprinkle with 1/2 of Kahlua, spread 1/2 of the pudding, 1/2 of the Cool Whip, 1/2 of the strawberries, 1/2 of Heath bar and all of the banana.
Continue one more layer of each (except banana), ending with Cool Whip, candy and strawberries.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken drummies
directions: Heat brown sugar and soy sauce to dissolve sugar.
Place chicken wings in baking dish.
Bake 3 hours at 325° or cook in crock-pot on slow.

title: chocolate chip cookies(heritage recipe)
directions: Add
shortening, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla, and mix thoroughly.
Add flour, soda, and salt. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.

title: velveeta ground beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix and sugar; add oil and stir.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat after each egg.
Add nectar and stir well.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken macaroni
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Let stand 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
May be made ahead of time and frozen.

title: cheesy lima bean casserole
directions: Drain lima beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Pour beans, liquid, chopped celery, onion powder, pepper, mayonnaise and 1/2 cup of cheese into greased casserole dish.
Stir to mix well.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Then spread crushed crackers over all.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 300° oven.
Double for larger casserole.

title: spaghetti bordelaise
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan over low heat.
Add olive oil, then garlic and salt.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes, stirring, until garlic is light brown.
Remove from heat and stir in parsley.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Roll bite sized chicken in flour and seasonings.
Brown in margarine.
Pour over chicken, water, bouillon cubes and Marsala wine.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Add flour to thicken (to form a paste).
Serve over bed of egg noodles with margarine.

title: water chestnuts appetizer
directions: Wrap chestnuts in thirds of bacon.
Line cookie sheet or broiler with foil.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Turn and bake 10 minutes.
Combine ketchup and sugars for sauce.
Place chestnuts in sauce and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen before baking or after.

title: tuna cashew casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, but noodles.
Put in casserole dish and cover with Chinese noodles.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: mammy's moist cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
When almost finished beating, add the pudding mix and beat until mixed well.
Batter will be thick.
Bake at 350° until done.
This recipe also makes good cupcakes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mushrooms.
Bring to a boil. Add mushrooms and simmer for 5 minutes.
Marinate at least overnight or longer.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats and buttermilk; let stand 10 minutes.
Add Egg Beaters, brown sugar and oil.
Stir until blended.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Spoon into muffin pan that has been Pam sprayed. Bake in preheated 350° oven about 15 minutes.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: rice and spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white salad
directions: Heat marshmallows in milk until dissolved.
Crumble cream cheese into this mixture, stirring until dissolved.
Stir all ingredients together gently.
Let set overnight in refrigerator. Makes very large quantity.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream well first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and flour to above ingredients.
Sift next 2 ingredients or stir together.
Add dry ingredients into creamed sugar and butter, alternating with sour cream.
Add vanilla.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs; add cream and flour.
Add rest of ingredients and boil 5 minutes.
Just before removing from stove, add 1 teaspoon each of salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Stir.
Can be kept a long time.

title: sweet cornbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until soft and combine.
Add eggs and beat.
Add cornmeal.
Sift and add remaining dry ingredients with milk.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chopped herring salad
directions: Drain herring and save liquid.
Put in Cuisinart with eggs, cored apple (cut into chunks) and bread (with crust removed) and combine with steel blade until it's as finely chopped as you like it.
Stir in some liquid from jar if the mixture is too thick. Chill and then serve.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all except egg whites, which are folded in last.
Put into baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 12.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix milk and marshmallows and melt marshmallows over low heat. Pour over other ingredients; mix well.
Put in cake pan (tube pan) and refrigerate for 24 hours before removing from pan.
Keep cake in refrigerator.

title: crunchy pea casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in 1/2 stick margarine.
Add next 5 ingredients; mix together and pour into buttered casserole. Melt remaining margarine and add stuffing; blend.
Place atop casserole.
Heat at 350° until warm (20 to 30 minutes).

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Put sugar and Karo into pan.
Bring to small boil.
Let cool. Add peanut butter and corn flakes.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Drop onto cookie sheet.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll out cookie dough on round baking sheets. Cook until lightly brown (like a big cookie). Let cool. Add Cool Whip and cream cheese together, then put on top of cookie. Add orange juice, sugar, water and cornstarch and cook until thick. Let it cool. While cooling, slice fruit, grapes in halves and strawberries and kiwi in several slices. Lay on top of cookie, making a circle of each fruit until you have covered the pizza. Then after glaze has cooled, pour over top.

title: barbecued sauce
directions: Cook onion in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer uncovered 15 minutes.

title: classic chocolate fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a metal bowl over hot (but not boiling) water, slowly melt chocolate, stirring gently. Cool. Grease two 9-inch round layer cake pans and line with waxed paper. In a large mixing bowl, cream butter; add sugar and eggs. Beat at high speed for five minutes until light and fluffy. Be sure to scrape bottom and sides of pan to mix thoroughly. Beat in vanilla and cooled chocolate. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt. Mix into creamed mixture alternating with sour cream, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. When thoroughly blended, stir in boiling water.
Batter will be thin. Pour immediately into prepared pans. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool in pans 15 minutes.
Finish cooling on wire racks.

title: seven layer magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 inch baking pan. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted butter, then pour milk over crumbs.
Top remaining ingredients in order listed.
Press cookie mixture down firmly into pan.
Bake for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool before cutting into bars.
Store in air tight container.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: maple syrup pie
directions: Beat ingredients together and pour into 3 pie shells.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Yields 3 pies.

title: asparagus - seashore style(microwave)
directions: Place asparagus in water.
Cook, uncovered, for 8 to 10 minutes.
Blend together the soup, cream cheese and cayenne pepper.
Stir in shrimp.
Place cooked asparagus in casserole dish and pour shrimp mixture on top.
Pour bread crumbs on top; sprinkle with paprika.
Cook on Full power for 4 to 5 minutes and serve.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel, cut in cubes and boil eggplant. Drain well and mash. Add oleo, salt and pepper to taste, onion and crackers or bread crumbs. Add sage and beaten egg. Add from 1/2 to 1 cup milk to make mixture like a thick batter. Do not make too thin. Pour into buttered casserole dish and sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: In a large bowl mix the popcorn, M&M's and peanuts.
Melt together the marshmallows, oleo and oil.
Stir in the popcorn mixture until coated.
Press into 2 greased 9 x 13-inch pans. Chill until it hardens.
Slice into squares with a sharp knife.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Beat the eggs until they are real thick.
Add salt and keep adding flour until they make a stiff dough.
Roll thin and cut in strips.
Let dry; then they are ready to use in soups.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello as directed.
Drain pineapple and blueberries and let set until jelled.
After it has jelled, add the cream cheese (with the sugar dissolved in it), sour cream, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and nuts, if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together and bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: spiced rubbed hens
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Rinse birds and pat dry.
Mix spices with salt and rub birds inside and out.
Place in a roasting pan.
Put pan in oven.
After 15 minutes or so, baste every 10 minutes or until juices run clear.

title: crock-pot on the go
directions: Crumble hamburger; chop onion.
Fry until browned well.
Drain fat.
Put in crock-pot.
Slice cheese into small squares.
Put cheese, soup and picante sauce in crock-pot; stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: In small bowl mix milk, Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar.
Whip with whisk or fork.
Pour over cauliflower, broccoli, cheese and bacon.
Toss together.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Reserve 1/2 of pecans to cover cheese ball.
Shape into ball.

title: pecan rolls
directions: In a saucepan, cook sugar, syrup and water to 256°.
Remove from heat; add Marshmallow Creme.
Do not stir.
Let creme set on the syrup for 10 minutes, stir well and beat.
Add flavoring and coloring as desired.
Beat with mixer at medium speed until mixture will break off when beaters are lifted.
Add shortening. Pour batch out on marble slab (or area that has been cooled with bagged ice), sprinkled with confectioners sugar.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed, stirring until just moistened.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Deep fry until brown; drain on paper towels.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Spread layers of cubed chicken and grated cheese over broccoli.
Mix chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and Pet milk.
Pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until top is slightly browned.

title: bread pudding
directions: Melt butter and blend together with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea special
directions: Fry bacon in a large skillet.
Remove and saute onion, bell pepper, bay leaf and celery in drippings until tender.
Add peas, tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover; simmer about 3 hours. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add sugar, milk and eggs.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Serve with or without frosting.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except candy, in large mixing bowl. Mix on lowest speed until completely mixed.
Make balls and roll in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet. Remove from oven and top immediately with a candy kiss.

title: congealed salad
directions: Stir jello into hot water.
Add fruit and nuts.
Mix together and pour into a flat dish.
Chill until firm.
Mix together softened cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Spread over chilled salad.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans. Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar, salt, cornstarch, and Karo until thick and clear.
Add jello and food coloring.
When slightly cool, add berries.
Put in a pie shell and garnish with Cool Whip.
Cool and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well.
Place into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Mix soup, mayonnaise, eggs and cheese. Pour over broccoli. Top with onions.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all the ingredients except for the pecan halves.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in pecan halves.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 35 minutes 325 to 350°.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onions, pepper and celery in butter until tender.
Add to cornbread and stir well.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
While beating, stir in mashed potatoes and spices, then add melted chocolate.
Sift flour and baking powder together and stir in nuts and raisins.
Mix with shortening mixture.
Can be baked in loaf pan or layer.
If baked in layers, chop nuts very fine.
Bake at 375°.

title: grandma's persimmon pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour 9 x 11 glass baking dish.
Combine beaten eggs and sugar; add persimmon pulp and mix well.
Add melted butter and mix.
Mix dry ingredients: flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with buttermilk, to pulp mixture.
Pour ingredients into baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour or until pudding pulls away from side of pan.
Cool before serving.

title: grandma's crumbly beans
directions: Cook flour and margarine until lightly browned.
Stir in all other ingredients, except cheese and corn flakes.
Pour into a greased 2 quart casserole; cover with cheese.
Mix corn flake crumbs with 1 tablespoon margarine (melted) and sprinkle on casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: apple muffins with coriander
directions: In a medium-size bowl, stir butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in egg and milk.
Blend well.
Stir in apples.
In a separate large bowl, blend flour, wheat germ, baking powder, spices and walnuts.
Make a well in center of dry mixture and add wet mixture all at once.
Stir until just blended.
Spoon batter into 1 dozen greased muffin cups until 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook potatoes in jackets until tender.
Peel and shred.
Combine with sour cream, onions, 3/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper. Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Can be refrigerated until time to bake. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese until softened.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallow cream and juice.
Mix well, then refrigerate.

title: wassail punch
directions: Heat ingredients to boil and simmer.
Prepare, 3 to 4 hours earlier, 2 oranges with cloves.
Boil in water.
Add this juice to punch.
Slice oranges and float on punch.
Makes 16 1/2 cups.

title: baked hash
directions: Ground corned beef with onion.
Boil potatoes, mash and mix with meat.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Mix well; put in baking pan.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fudge pie
directions: Stir until well blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° 35 to 40 minutes or until firm.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: *To toast, place in a dry saut pan and cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes or until brown.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Cook over boiling water until thick.

title: pears in chocolate sauce
directions: If you don't have vanilla sugar, just use regular sugar and vanilla extract.

title: custard pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs, add sugar, cornstarch, salt, milk and stir well.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
bake in 450 degree oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350 degrees for 3/4 of an hour.

title: baked indian pudding
directions: Pour into a quart of boiling milk over a pint of corn meal. Let it stand to cool.
Take 1/2 pint of molasses or enough to sweeten the pudding.
Put 1 tablespoon of butter with molasses and let it melt on the stove.
Put in three well-beaten eggs without separating the whites and yolks.
Mix well, adding some grated lemon peel and raisins.
Bake slowly 1 hour.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute garlic and green onions (to your preference).
Add shrimp and cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove shrimp and set aside.
Squeeze half the lemon over the shrimp and add the other half to the sauce.
Stir in milk and thicken with cornstarch dissolved in water.
Season to taste.
Serve over cooked rice or angel hair pasta.

title: lime pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; add water to make one cup.
Boil.
Add marshmallows and jello; stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold water and chill until partially set.
Soften cream cheese; stir in pineapple and chopped nuts.
Add jello mixture and refrigerate overnight.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix preceding ingredients in 9-inch pie plate and press around sides to form crust.
Bake until brown at 350°.
Cool.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and add sugar.
Grind cranberries and apples.
Add to Jell-O with pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and vanilla. Spread over Jell-O.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; pick off bone.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
