Mix cream of chicken and mushroom soups with 1 can of broth. Pour over chicken.
Mix 2 cups of broth with eggs and cornbread stuffing mix.
Spread over soup and chicken.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°.

title: spaghetti and tomatoes
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse.
Put a layer of spaghetti in a buttered baking dish. Cover it with a layer of White Sauce II, using strained canned tomatoes instead of milk.
Dot with bacon and onions that have been sauteed together in a skillet until the bacon is crisp. Repeat layers until dish is full.
A little grated cheese may be sprinkled on each layer of tomatoes if desired.
Cover with seasoned bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: delicious white cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in alternately with milk and flavoring. Fold in egg whites beaten stiffly. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers or 35 to 45 minutes for oblong.

title: orange jello
directions: First Layer:
Mix Jell-O and let set until thickened.
Drain and save pineapple juice.
Add pineapple, apples and marshmallows. Put in refrigerator and get firm.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Use 2 tablespoons per cup.
Hot, aromatic and yummy.

title: slick dumplings
directions: Mix together all ingredients until you have a smooth dough. Roll out on a well-floured bread board until paper thin.
Cut into strips and drop into your desired boiling broth.
Cook until tender, about 15 minutes.

title: large pound cake
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients together well.
Add flour and milk alternately with vanilla last.
Mix 10 minutes.
Turn mixer on very high for 2 minutes.
Bake in a large greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: three bean salad
directions: Stir vinegar into sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add oil, salt and pepper and mix together well.
Add drained beans and sliced onion.
I sometimes add a can of garbanzo beans.
Chill.

title: my best gingerbread(this recipe is over 100 years old.)
directions: Cream together butter or shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, salt and cloves. Combine hot water and molasses.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the liquid mixture a little at a time, beating after each addition.
Bake in a greased paper-lined 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 16.
Serve with whipped cream or other whipped topping.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar. Squeeze the lemon juice and use pulp. Combine ingredients and bake in raw pie shell for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sourdough starter and bread
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
warm water.
Add sugar and instant potato flakes; mix well.
Keep Starter in glass jar with holes in
lid. Store
in refrigerator 5 days.
After 5 days, remove from refrigerator and feed with the following:

title: curried rice
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil in a medium saucepan.
Add Curried Rice Mix.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: golden sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes and mash.
Whip in butter and milk; add sugar, salt and spices.
Fold in 1/2 cut up marshmallows.
Pile lightly in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; remove and add rest of marshmallows on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer, until marshmallows brown.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Crumble together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix all the ingredients together in order.
Bake for 8 minutes.

title: bisquick sausage balls
directions: Mix well with fingers.
Shape into 3/4 to 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pork and tomatillo casserole
directions: Fry tortillas lightly in oil and drain.
Wilt onion in oil. Add tomatillo, garlic and dash of salt.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Set aside.
Mix sour cream and chilies.

Set aside. Butter 2-quart casserole dish and arrange alternate layers of tortillas, tomatillo sauce, pork, zucchini and sour cream mixture and olives until all ingredients have been used, ending with a layer of sour cream mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: no cook chocolate mousse
directions: Blend together first four ingredients in blender 2 minutes. Bring the heavy cream to a boil; add to chocolate mixture.
Pour into sherbet dishes.

title: soy chicken wings
directions: Flour
and brown in fat the chicken wings.
Lay flat in baking dish;
crumble
brown
sugar and chicken bouillon cube over wings.
Mix vinegar and soy sauce; pour over wings.
Bake for
45 minutes at 375°.
Serve with rice and stir fry vegetables.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix eggs, crackers, bread with diced onion, 1/2 of package onion soup mix, shave 1/4 of green pepper very fine into mix with 1 1/2 pounds ground chuck.
Place in bread pan, pack firmly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix 1 teaspoon horseradish with 1 teaspoon mustard, 1/2 cup ketchup and maple syrup.
Spread over top of meat loaf and bake for 15 minutes more then serve.

title: mary's cheese ball
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cool, shape into ball and roll in pecans.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and evaporated milk together until soft ball forms in water (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Pour over remaining ingredients and stir until marshmallows are melted.
Spread in buttered pan.
Cut in squares when cool enough to cut.

title: melting lace
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 cookie sheets; set aside.
In a medium saucepan, melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except chocolate.
Drop batter by level teaspoon 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 6 at a time.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven.
Let stand for 1 minute, then quickly remove to flat surface to cool.
Melt chocolate over hot, not boiling, water.
With small spatula, spread chocolate on one cookie and sandwich with another.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush cookies in glass cake pan to make crust. Press flat. Save a little to sprinkle on top. Chill while you mix together milk and pudding mix; set aside.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In a 3-quart shallow baking dish, mix soups, milk, pepper, thyme, vegetables and cooked cut up chicken. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; stir. Arrange biscuits around edge of pan and bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix well.
Can be used over grated cabbage or can be used for potato salad.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on box; drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, undrained fruit, 1 cup of coconut and eggs. Blend; beat at medium speed 2 minutes and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: spicy cheese ball
directions: Let cheese warm to room temperature and cream with cream cheese.
Add onion powder, garlic sauce and Worcestershire sauce. Form into small ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Sprinkle cheese ball with chili powder and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil first five items together for 2 minutes.
Add oats to mixture and spread on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: shirley's apple cake
directions: Peel apples and slice thin.
Mix apples with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.

title: bean dip for tortillas
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed.
Chill and serve with tortilla chips.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In medium saucepan melt butter and chocolate.
Add sugar 1/2 cup at a time.
Add salt in conjunction with sugar.
Sugar should be completely moistened.
After each addition, mixture will be thick and dry.
Slowly stir in evaporated milk a little at a time. Add vanilla.
May be served chilled.

title: fragrance balls
directions: You will need ribbon and netting.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Combine stuffing, butter, broth, diced chicken or turkey, green onion, celery, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs and milk and pour over chicken mixture. Spread soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over casserole and bake additional 5 minutes.

title: stuffed bell peppers(make ahead and freeze.)
directions: Clean peppers by cutting around stem and removing pith, leaving pepper whole.
Parboil 10 minutes.
In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion until beef loses redness.
Drain and rinse beef.
Return it to pan.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese. Cook over medium heat 10 minutes longer.
Stuff peppers with equal portions of mixture.
Arrange peppers in 7 x 11-inch glass baking dish so that they support one another.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with cheese last 10 minutes of cooking.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix together lemon and orange jello and 9 cups of water. Bring sugar and 4 cups of water to boil and take off heat.
Mix the jello and water mixture with this.
Add juice to mixture and freeze in containers.
Will still be good for at least 6 months in the freezer.
When ready to serve, take from freezer, let thaw and add ginger ale to taste.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, milk, vanilla and salt.
Put coconut in unbaked crust.
Pour mixture over coconut.
Then cut margarine on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat softened cream cheese, Karo and brown sugar until sugar is smooth.
With mixer at medium speed, add 3/4 cup milk and vanilla.
Beat until blended. Stir in 1 cup chopped pecans.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: creamy au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 1-quart casserole.
In saucepan, over medium heat, cook frozen onion until tender.
Stir in undiluted soup and cream cheese cubes. Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and hot.

In casserole, alternately layer frozen potatoes and hot cream sauce, ending with a sauce layer. Cover and bake 45 minutes or until sauce is bubbly and potatoes are tender. Remove from oven and sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwich
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add enough mayonnaise to hold together.
Use seasoned salt to taste.
Spread on bun halves and bake in 350° oven until cheese begins to melt.

title: great grandma's freezer pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions approximately 1 gallon.
Mix with salt and refrigerate overnight.
Drain in morning and rinse.
If too salty, rinse again.
Heat vinegar and sugar until dissolved and cool to lukewarm.
Pour over cucumbers.
Freeze in plastic container.
Defrost before use.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar together.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 11-inch dish and chill until firm.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Prepare in crock-pot.
Put all vegetables in crock-pot for several hours on low heat.
Mix occasionally.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Roll out the crescent rolls onto a cookie sheet and bake to directions on package.
Cut up vegetables into small pieces.
Mix cream cheese (room temperature), dressing and mayonnaise. When crescent rolls are cooled, spread cream cheese mixture evenly on top.
Top with cut vegetables.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours, then cut into squares.
Enjoy!

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, crushed potato chips and butterscotch chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: raisin bars
directions: Boil raisins and water 10 minutes and cool.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, raisins and water, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, baking soda and vanilla.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg and beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients; beat just a little.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: (kids) microwave s'mores
directions: On a graham cracker, put the same size of chocolate bar. Place 2 marshmallows on top of chocolate.
Microwave for 15 to 30 seconds or until marshmallow softens.
Place another graham cracker on top and press.
Enjoy; its very good.

title: cream pie
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients slowly, stirring steadily.
Set off; add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Fix whites.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine milk, sugar, eggs and oleo.
Cook over medium heat. Stir until thick, about 15 minutes, like pudding.
Add coconut, pecans, sugar and vanilla. Stir until spreading consistency. Cool.

title: 7-up red satin punch
directions: Chill fruit juices and 7-Up.
Prepare 7-Up "ice" cubes by pouring additional 7-Up into 2 ice trays and freezing.
At serving time, combine juices in a punch bowl.
Slowly pour in chilled 7-Up.
Add "ice" cubes.
Makes about 35 servings.

title: pecan coconut pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, corn syrup, butter, vanilla, and salt; mix well.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Pour into pastry shell.
Make a domed cover with foil.
Bake 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover, bake 10-15 minutes longer or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 6-8.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook macaroni, cool.
Cook beef and drain mix off in taco seasoning.
Add together and stir in dressing.
Stir in taco chips before serving.

title: gourmet goulash
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch cubes.
Melt butter in a saucepan and brown meat.
Add onions, lightly saute.
Stir in salt, pepper, flour and paprika.
Add wine, sour cream and tomato sauce.
Stir to blend smoothly.
Turn the mixture into a casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: spaghetti sauce(makes 100 servings)
directions: Cook 7 pounds of spaghetti in boiling water. Drain. Add to sauce.
Use two 6-inch steam table pans.

title: curried fruit
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar and curry powder.
Drain fruit well and put in a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool and refrigerate.
Reheat and serve.
May use any fruit except fruit cocktail.

title: orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare tube pan; grease well.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, peppers and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, cream, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Toss with chicken mixture.
Add nuts and grapes just before serving.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Smooth soups and vegetables over chicken.
Make crust by mixing flour and margarine.
Pour over soups.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 45 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: sensibly delicious double chocolate chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1 cup chocolate chips, sugar, applesauce and margarine until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add egg whites; stir well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in pan and bake 16 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery in oleo until soft, but not browned. Mix with cornbread, salt, poultry seasoning, black pepper and sage.
Add eggs.
Warm soup with chicken broth and add.
Cut up chicken and add to mixture.
Bake until done at 350°.

title: roasted red potatoes
directions: Try to get potatoes of a smallish nature. Boil or steam whole potatoes until almost fork-tender, then drain - may be done an hour in advance. You want finished pieces about the size of a golf ball, so if larger, cut to approximate size.

Lightly film a heavy baking dish with good quality extra virgin olive oil. Toss in the potatoes. Salt them and you can add chopped herb like fresh rosemary, if you wish. Roast in 400° oven for about 20 minutes or until they begin to brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat, drain and season.
Mix soups and meat.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and top with frozen Tater Tots.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes at 400° or until Tater Tots are done.

title: banana currant muffins
directions: Combine flours, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In another bowl, combine buttermilk, oil, bananas and egg whites; add to dry mixture.
Stir until all ingredients are moist.
Fold in currants.
Fill paper-lined muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Cool and serve.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When done, punch holes in cake.	Let cool.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle chocolate chips on top of Cool Whip.

title: sweet-sour meatballs
directions: Cook noodles.
In Dutch oven or large casserole, toss meat with browning sauce.
Mix in cereal.
Add all the remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until the meat and vegetables are tender
Serves with noodles.
Yields 8 servings.

title: irish spaghetti
directions: Brown chopped meat in pan.

Add 2 cans sauce and 2 cans water. Simmer; add chopped peppers and 1/2 package Cheddar cheese, cut up. Cook over low flame until peppers are tender and cheese is melted. Cook spaghetti the regular way.
Drain and cut up spaghetti.
Put in oven casserole and add meat mixture.
Mix. Put rest of the cheese on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes.
Serves 4 persons.

title: ritzy vegetable casserole
directions: Drain and pour into shallow baking pan the frozen vegetables, garlic powder, basil and parsley.
Mix cheddar cheese, mayonnaise, onions, water chestnuts and garlic powder.
Spread cheese mixture on top of vegetables.
Mix Ritz crackers and melted margarine.
Sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and coat chicken well.
(Shake in a
plastic bag.)
Place chicken in pan and bake at 425° for 35 minutes.
Turn and bake until done, about 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Place bacon strips in bottom of cooking vessel and put in oven.
Heat until bacon is warm enough to thoroughly grease pan.
Remove bacon and set aside.
In a bowl, mix pork and beans, tomato sauce, mustard and vinegar.
Add brown sugar to taste (it takes a good amount of sugar to make it taste good).
It will be quite soupy.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients, except coconut, in blender.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour in greased 9-inch pie pan. Let set for 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add quartered artichokes and stir over low heat for 15 minutes. Continue to cook and stir in Cheddar and Romano cheeses.
Add hot sauce, then add bread crumbs and mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish; sprinkle with additional bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: grilled corn and black bean salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and serve.

title: egg pie
directions: Bake in uncooked pie shell at 350° until brown.

title: pulled candy
directions: Cook sugar, vinegar, water and butter together until it forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Do not stir.
Pour onto buttered plate.
Pull when cool enough to handle.

title: sesame flounder
directions: Place fillets in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Drizzle with lemon juice; sprinkle with pepper.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in apple juice concentrate until crisp-tender; spoon over fillets.
Sprinkle with sesame seed; bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
(Yields 8 servings, 130 calories per 3-ounce serving.)

title: grape salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Store in refrigerator.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and molasses.
Sift together and add dry ingredients.
Mix and add hot water last. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tina's strawberry pizza
directions: Crust:
Mix evenly flour, nuts and margarine.
Spread on 13-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: crustless pie
directions: Pour all of the ingredients into a bowl.
Mix on medium speed for approximately 1 minute.
Pour into greased and lightly floured glass Pyrex pie plate.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Melt lard and oleo.
Add sugar, egg and milk.
Blend. Dissolve soda in 2 tablespoons of warm water and add to other liquids.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well and drop on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fluffy mustard sauce
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and cook over hot water stirring constantly until thick, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, blend in oleo and horseradish.
Fold in whipped cream.
Serve with warm meat (especially good with ham).

title: turkey rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, heat soups, milk, turkey, cheese and broccoli.
Stir often.
Add seasonings.
Spray a baking dish with nonstick oil.
Spoon cooked rice into dish and pour sauce over and gently mix together.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together until well coated with mayonnaise.
Cover in a large bowl and put in refrigerator.
Let set overnight.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Combine egg, salt, lemon juice and 1/4 cup oil in blender container.
Blend together until mixture begins to thicken. Blend in remaining 3/4 cup oil, pouring in a thin stream until mixture is thick and smooth, about 2 minutes.
(Allow slightly longer beating time for rotary or electric beater.)
Makes about 1 cup.

title: seasoned rice
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine soup mix, bouillon cube and water.
Heat to boiling over medium-high heat.
Stir in rice. Cover.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Preparation time: 5 minutes.
Cook: 25 minutes.

title: pork roast(with tangerine peel & thyme)
directions: Place trimmed pork loin on a wire rack in a 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
In a small bowl, combine, rind, thyme, salt & pepper and rub mixture over all sides of pork.
Set in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Add broth to the pan and roast the pork uncovered in a 350° oven, or until a meat thermometer registers 160°.
When done, transfer to a cutting board and let stand 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato and apple cobbler
directions: Mix the chunks of apples and potatoes in a 9-inch pie pan and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of the sugar.
Mix the remaining sugar, oat bran, oatmeal and cinnamon in a bowl.
Work the margarine in a bit at a time until the mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle the crumbs over the apples and potatoes.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Bake about 50 minutes, or until the potatoes are tender and the topping is browned.
Serve when still warm.

title: raspberry chiffon pie
directions: Puree raspberries in blender.
Strain to remove seeds. Discard seeds.
Measure 2/3 cup of puree for pie.
Refrigerate remaining puree to garnish pie.
Put raspberry flavored gelatin in medium size mixing bowl.
Add hot water while stirring constantly to soften and dissolve gelatin.
Stir in lemon juice and 2/3 cup raspberry puree.
Chill until partially set, 45 to 60 minutes.
Add salt to egg whites in a large mixing bowl.
Beat on low speed until frothy.
Increase to high speed and beat until soft peaks result, another 1 to 2 minutes.
Continue beating while gradually adding sugar.
Beat to stiff peaks, another minute or two.
Beat chilled raspberry mixture 30 seconds.
Fold in 1/2 cup whipped cream to
lighten mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour into 10-inch baked pie crust.
Chill 3 to 4 hours until set.

title: chicken and wine
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Layer sliced onions on bottom of roasting pan.
Arrange chicken breasts on top of onion.
Arrange potatoes and carrots around chicken.
In a bowl, mix garlic, chicken broth, white wine and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Sprinkle thyme, salt and pepper over chicken and vegetables.
Roast for 45 to 60 minutes or until juices run clear.

title: dressing for turkey
directions: Make cornbread loaf the night before.
Crumble cornbread and mix ingredients.
Preheat oven on 500°.
Pour cornbread in pan and bake at 500° for 10 minutes.
Cut down to 300° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: easy pineapple salad
directions: Drain the juice from the pineapple chunks.
To the juice, add sugar, flour, eggs and butter.
Cook until thick.
Cool; add the pineapple chunks, marshmallows and bananas (sliced) just before serving.

title: cinnamon apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange apple slices in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour water over top.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a hard boil.
Add crackers.
Boil hard for 2 minutes without stirring.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; dot with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 15 additional minutes.
Tastes like apple pie.

title: plantation peach shortcake
directions: First, cut up sweetened peaches, about 8 cups.
Sift dry ingredients; cut in brown sugar and shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add pecans.
Combine egg and cream.
Add to flour shortening mixture.
Mix until all flour is moist.
Spread dough in 2 greased round layer cake pans.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Place peaches between layers.
Top with whipped cream.

title: the best old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Lightly grease casserole dish.
Cube bread.
Heat milk to scalding, pour over bread.
Let cool and add butter, sugar, eggs, salt, raisins and cinnamon.
Stir all.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: grilled ham
directions: Put steak in a large shallow dish.
Mix together ginger ale, orange juice, brown sugar, vegetable oil, white vinegar, mustard, ginger and cloves, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour over steak.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Turn meat occasionally. Drain steak; grill covered, over hot coals, 15 minutes on each side.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all and pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bread pudding
directions: Note:
Coconut or raisins can be added for variety.

title: skip and go naked
directions: Note: Whatever size frozen lemonade you use, that is your measurement for the rest of ingredients.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Slice zucchini lengthwise into 1/2-inch slices.
Blanch zucchini 3 minutes in boiling water.
Cool in ice water to stop cooking.
Combine cottage cheese, Romano cheese, parsley, egg and Italian seasoning.
Place half of zucchini slices in casserole dish.
Spoon cheese mix over zucchini slices, then layer remaining zucchini slices, sauce and Mozzarella.
Bake at 375°
until zucchini is heated through.

title: italian chicken
directions: Soak chicken pieces in beaten egg for 30 minutes.
Gently roll chicken in bread crumbs.
Fry chicken in melted butter until browned.
Place in casserole and cover with sauteed mushrooms and broth.
Top with thinly sliced cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° To double the recipe, double everything except the eggs.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook the ground beef in the microwave for 5 minutes on High. Drain.
Mix the margarine, onion and green chili pepper together; cook on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, then add the tomato sauce, taco mix and the water.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Beat 2 eggs with a wire whisk.
Add 1 cup half and half, then add to other ingredients.

title: *red cabbage with apples
directions: Put shredded cabbage in kettle.
Add boiling water and cook, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add apples and cook for 10 minutes or until tender.
Add the rest of the ingredients combined.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy broccoli or cauliflower soup
directions: Put all ingredients in your crock-pot on low for supper in the morning.
For lunch, turn the crock-pot on high.

title: raspberry tartlets
directions: Prepare single pie crust according to directions and divide in half.
Roll out 1/2 to 1/8 inch thick.
Cut into 3-inch rounds. Place one teaspoon of filling in the center of each round.
Fold in half and seal edges with fork.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients over low heat until bubbly.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cool water. Add to pumpkin mixture and cool. Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/3 cup sugar and melted butter; press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat 2 eggs; add 3/4 cup sugar and cream cheese. Mix until until smooth; spread over first layer. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Beat egg whites (room temperature) until frothy.
Add sugar. Beat until thick. Fold into cool pumpkin mixture. Spread over first two layers. Top with medium size carton Cool Whip. Keep refrigerated.

title: tarragon chicken salad
directions: Shred chicken into bite sized pieces.
Whisk sour cream and mayonnaise together and pour over chicken.
Add other ingredients and toss well.
Refrigerate, covered, for at least
4 hours.

title: orange cooler
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; blend until ice cubes are crushed and mixture is foamy.
Serve in tall glass.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: In a small saucepan, melt peanut butter and butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Stir in milk. Add more milk, if necessary, until of spreading consistency. Makes about 1 cup.

title: pork casserole
directions: Brown pork in oil in a large skillet.
Add onion, celery and green pepper; saute until vegetables are tender.
Stir in salt, pepper, basil and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes.
Stir in soup, milk and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: mustard bread
directions: Spread bread lightly with mustard; cut each slice into 4 squares.
Arrange squares on baking sheet; top with pickle slices and mound of deviled ham.
Broil until bread is toasted and meat is heated through.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Add dash of salt, corn syrup and melted butter.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and warm in a large pan.

title: combination salad
directions: Wash
lettuce
thoroughly and shred. Add tomatoes, bell pepper rings, onion, radishes, carrots, sugar and cheese.
Mix with mayonnaise and salt.
Serve in individual bowls.
Yields 6 to 8 (6 ounce) bowls.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Pour this mixture over chicken; bake until brown at 350°, for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: cranberry pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. In large bowl, beat the eggs with a fork, just until blended. Stir in the corn syrup, brown sugar, butter and orange peel.
Sprinkle the cranberries in the pie crust. Arrange pecan halves on top of cranberries. Pour syrup mixture carefully over pecans. Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until filling is set.
If the edge of the pie crust browns too quickly, cover with a strip of foil to prevent further browning.

title: hard christmas candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to hard crack stage using candy thermometer.
Remove from heat, add oil and food coloring for color desired.
Pour into large buttered pan.
Let set for 1 minute.
Cover a dough board with powdered sugar.
Pour candy on board.
Start cutting candy with scissors, work fast as candy sets fast.

title: iowa brownies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Then add syrup and the eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: judy's "mounds"
directions: Mix coconut and syrup together.
Blend well.
Let set for 10 minutes in refrigerator.
Form into balls and place on waxed paper.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Melt chocolate with paraffin in top of double boiler.
Dip coconut balls into chocolate using toothpick.
After chocolate hardens, refrigerate.

title: baked salmon croquettes
directions: Preheat oven to 400° (after mixture has chilled).
Drain salmon.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: country potato soup
directions: In large saucepan combine first six ingredients, cover and cook until potatoes are done, about 20 minutes. Potatoes should be Idaho so as not to get mushy. Add one cup milk, heat. In medium bowl, mix sour cream, flour and remaining milk. Strain carefully then add to soup base, stirring constantly, then add chives and dill. Cook over low heat until thick.

title: soul-style sweet potatoes
directions: Rinse the potato slices in ample water and drain.
Place in a 2-quart covered saucepan and add the water, sugar and butter. Cover and simmer until very tender, about 30 minutes.
Do not stir during the cooking process.

title: sauerkraut with polish sausage
directions: Mix all together, except cheese.
Cook in crock-pot for 8 hours on low.
At the end, add the cheese.

title: hamburger tater tot casserole
directions: Spread ground chuck in bottom of a casserole dish and compress.
Spread the cream soups over meat.
Top with Tater Tots. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.

title: jack's favorite peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter until crumbly.
Pat 2/3 of the mixture in pie shell.
Make pudding as per directions and pour over mixture in pie shell.
Spread Cool Whip over top of pudding. Sprinkle remaining powdered sugar-peanut butter mixture on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: microwave mini meat loaf for one
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small mixing bowl; mix well. Press into 6 to 8 ounce microwave-safe mug or custard cup.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until cooked in center (150°), rotating mug once.
Drain the juices; invert onto serving plate.
Serve with additional catsup, if desired.
Makes 1 serving.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Grind cookies in food processor or blender.
Mix with melted butter and press into 10-inch spring-form pan.
Chill 1/2 hour; hurry it up in freezer.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Remove from heat and cool a bit.
Add the 2 whole eggs and mix well.
Add egg yolks and mix very well.
Beat cream (2 cups) with the powdered sugar until soft peaks form.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Lighten chocolate mixture by stirring in a little of the egg whites and a little of the cream.
Fold in remaining egg whites and remaining cream.
Pour into chilled crumb crust.
Chill overnight (or at least 6 hours).

title: tropical trifle
directions: Combine milk and cornstarch in a saucepan; mix until cornstarch is completely dissolved.
Add sugar, egg whites and oil; mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium-low heat.
Beat constantly until thickened.
Add extracts.

title: texas tomato tea sandwiches
directions: Slice the tomatoes thinly, lightly salt and place on a baking sheet that has been lined with paper towels. Let the tomatoes drain for several hours.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix.
Bake as directed on cake mix package.
Cool completely.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, cream oleo, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour, potato chips and nuts.
Mix well.

title: egg casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cut 1 pound of Velveeta cheese in cubes.
Place on top of bread.
Sprinkle onion, green pepper, pimento, mushrooms, ham, sausage or bacon on top of cheese.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Cut velveeta into chunks.
Combine all ingredients in crockpot.
Turn on high heat.
Stir occasionally, until melted and well blended.
Simmer on low.
Serve with chips.

title: chi chi beef
directions: Heat oil in skillet or wok.
Add onions and ginger root, stir-fry 1 minute.
Add beef, stir-fry 2 minutes or until brown. In a separate bowl, mix together sugar, soy sauce, sherry, water and red pepper flakes until sugar dissolves.
Add to wok.
Lower heat and simmer (covered) for 30 minutes.
Uncover, increase heat to high, cook until sauce thickens, about 30 minutes.
Remove from skillet or wok.
Serve hot.
Makes approximately 40 pieces.

title: banana tea bread(sugar-free and low calorie)
directions: Combine shortening, eggs, liquid sweetener and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Fold in mashed bananas.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Crusty and golden outside.
Makes 12 servings.
Each 123 calories.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Mix strawberries, grapes, peaches and bananas together and spoon fruit mixture into lettuce cup.
Makes 5 servings (210 calories).

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, margarine and nuts.
Press in the bottom of an oblong pan.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over the first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin or squash cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese and sugar first, then add rest of ingredients. Pour into shell and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate, cherry, chocolate chip, brownie cake
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients.
Spread into greased and floured large (11 x 17-inch) jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle next 3 ingredients on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Watch closely.

title: beefy cream cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave for about 30 seconds in small mixing bowl.
Add green onions, chipped beef, Worcestershire and garlic.
Serve chilled with Ritz crackers.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburg and onion; drain fat.
Add all remaining ingredients (except rolls);
stir and simmer until pepper is tender.
Serve over hamburg rolls.

title: pandesal
directions: Thaw dough at room temperature for several hours.
On a lightly floured surface, roll dough to form a cylinder about 2-inches in diameter.
Combine bread crumbs and salt.
Roll dough in crumb mixture.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Lay cut side up in a greased cookie sheet.
Cover with a dishcloth and let rise in a warm place for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake rolls for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: twice baked spuds
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, bake potatoes in a 350° oven until tender.
Cool slightly, then halve each potato lengthwise. Scoop potato into a medium bowl, reserving skins.
Thinly slice green onion, reserving some for garnish.
With electric mixer, whip potatoes, buttermilk, margarine, green onion, pepper and a little salt, if desired.
Spoon into potato skins.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and paprika.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden.
Sprinkle with green onion.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple cake square
directions: Mix in this order:
eggs, sugar and flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients:
flour, soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix well. Add apple and mix well.
Add pecans and mix well.
Add Wesson oil and mix well.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 or 35 minutes.
Do not open oven for 30 minutes while baking . Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan which has been greased and sprinkled with flour.
Let cool slightly before cutting in squares.
Keep covered to stay moist.

title: cabbage with a flair
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add vegetables, condiments and cook, covered, until tender.
Do not add liquid, but cook in vegetables' own juice.

title: banana maple walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour 9x5x3-inch loaf pan and set aside.
Cream butter with sugar in large mixer bowl until smooth.
Add egg, maple flavor extract, vanilla, and cinnamon.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed 2 minutes. Add bananas and sour cream and mix well.
Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to banana mixture and mix well. Stir in walnuts and spoon into prepared pan.
Bake 65 to 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on rack.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until light.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour.
Spoon mixture into greased tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.
Cool in pan for 15 to 20 minutes before removing.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bone and cut into bite size pieces, cook in small amount of oleo until white on both sides.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cook broccoli in salted water, drain.
Place on top of chicken.
Melt oleo in saucepan on medium heat, blend in flour.
Add cheese and broth; cook until thick.
Add whipping cream; stir until smooth.
Put over chicken and broccoli.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: favorite casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions until done. Cook macaroni in a large pot. Drain and add meat mixture and all other ingredients, reserving 1 cup of shredded extra sharp cheese. Pour into a large Pyrex dish and sprinkle top with remaining cup of cheese. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: classic chocolate mousse
directions: Absolutely no sugar, no butter and no water required.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; keep juice.
Combine sugar and flour.
Add 3 to 5 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Stir until well mixed.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Pour into baking dish.
Combine melted butter and crumbs.
Spread over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until brown.

title: company french toast
directions: Mix cinnamon, butter and brown sugar.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together eggs, milk and salt.
Place bread into pan over cinnamon sugar mixture.
Pour milk and egg mixture over the bread.
Cover and let set in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until golden and bubbly.
Invert on serving dish and cut into serving pieces.

title: quick-n-easy pepper jelly
directions: Add hot sauce of choice to jar of apple jelly to taste.
Add more if you want it hotter.
Pour this over block of cream cheese and serve with snack crackers of your choice.
Makes a delicious, quick, easy snack.

title: asparagus with sunshine sauce
directions: Cook asparagus.
In small saucepan, pour wine over onion. Stir in lemon juice and mayonnaise; heat just to boiling.
Gently stir in eggs.
Serve hot over spears.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in pan and boil until soft-ball stage on medium.
Take off stove and mix peanut butter and vanilla in hot mixture.
Pour in buttered glass dish and let cool.
Cut and enjoy!

title: caramel dipped apples
directions: Melt caramels and milk in microwave.
Cut apples in wedges. Dip apples in melted mixture.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In boiling salted water, cook peppers for 3 - 5 minutes. Remove and set aside.
In a skillet, cook beef, onion, and garlic until meat is done and onion is tender.
Drain any fat.
Add seasonings and soup; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese; cook and stir until melted.
Stir in rice.
Fill peppers; place in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 8.

title: talarena
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water for 15 minutes; drain.
Chop and brown onion, pepper and garlic cloves in fat.
Add tomatoes to onion mixture when browned.
Simmer for a few minutes.

title: quick chocolate fluff
directions: Melt chocolate.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Put into individual dessert cups and chill.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.
Serves 4.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix well and shape into loaf.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in jar.
Cover; shake vigorously. Add mushrooms; chill to blend flavors.
Shake again before tossing with salad greens, shrimp, tomatoes and onion.
Makes 8 servings (about 8 cups).

title: sorghum molasses pie
directions: Mix and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.

title: one pan pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Stir all ingredients, except raisins, in pan with fork until moistened; beat vigorously 1 minute.
Stir in raisins. Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Saut the onion in the margarine. Mix in the cream cheese, cottage cheese, egg and basil. Mix together the shrimp soup, milk, white wine, shrimp and crab meat. Grease 9 x 11 baking dish. Spread layer of the soup mixture over bottom of pan. Add uncooked noodles. Alternate the cream cheese mixture with the soup mixture. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: ground turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands thoroughly.
Place in 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven, uncovered, 50 to 60 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Cool and crumble 1/2 in punch bowl.
Top with 1 can pie filling and 1/2 each of pudding, pineapple, bananas and Cool Whip.
Repeat, using rest of everything.
Garnish with chopped pecans and coconut.

title: applesauce biscuits or bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: In a 3-quart microproof casserole, combine onion, green pepper and margarine.
Microwave at High for 1 to 2 minutes or until tender.
Stir in beans, corn syrup and mustard.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave, stirring once, 12 to 14 minutes, or until heated.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt beth's brown rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
In a casserole, put sauteed onion, rice, beef consomme and water.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: 24 hour layer lettuce salad
directions: Layer as follows:
lettuce, onion, peas and bacon.
Spread the mayo evenly over the salad.
Sprinkle the sugar evenly over the mayo.
Top with the crumbled bacon.
Cover and chill overnight. Enjoy!

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Melt shortening and oleo. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: oven baked brisket(very easy and great tasting)
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour over brisket. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: stir-fried shrimp and vegetables
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet or wok.
Add onion; stir for 3 minutes on medium-high heat.
Add shrimp, broccoli, bean sprouts and Chinese cabbage all at the same time.
Stir while food is frying on medium-high heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce; stir for 1 minute and remove.
Serve with brown rice.

title: green peas with tomatoes and mint
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and cook 5 to 7 minutes, until golden brown.
Stir in tomatoes and cook 3 minutes, then stir in peas, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring once or twice, until peas are hot. Remove from heat.
Stir in mint.

title: apple torte
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and mix well.
Stir in apples and pecans.
Lightly spray 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: my own special browned rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add sliced mushrooms and poultry seasoning.
Add water, about 1/2 cup at a time, until vegetables are soft, then add beef broth, a cup of water and Gravy Master.
When it comes to a boil, add rice.
Cook until liquid is absorbed.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix in blender in the order given.
Turn to high speed and count slowly to 10.
Pour into greased Pyrex pie plate and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This bubbles up and then settles down, forming a crust, custard filling with coconut topping.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, sugar and salt.
Beat together water, eggs and vinegar.
Mix well.
Combine with flour mixture.
Mix well. Mold in ball.
Chill before rolling into crusts.
Makes 3 (9-inch) single crusts.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix in 2-quart saucepan first 4 ingredients.
Stir constantly until thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and keep hot in 400° oven.
Cut shortening into flour, sugar, baking powder and salt until resembles fine crumbs. Stir in milk.
Drop dough into hot mixture in 6 spoonfuls.
Bake until topping is golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sherried artichoke chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken generously with salt, pepper and paprika to taste.
Brown chicken on all sides in
4 tablespoons butter. Transfer to casserole.
Arrange artichoke hearts between chicken pieces.
Add remaining butter to drippings in frying pan; add mushrooms and onion and saute until just tender.
Sprinkle flour over mushrooms and onions and stir in bouillon and sherry.
Cook, stirring well, for a few minutes, until flour is all integrated and sauce is smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in moderate oven, 375°, for 40 minutes or until chicken is tender. Serves 4.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in 1/2 cup candies.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate with remaining candies.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Saute onions in frypan, set aside.
Cook bacon and set aside. Drain grease and brown pork chops on both sides.
Mix sauerkraut, onions, crumbled bacon and caraway seed, tossing well.
Line a casserole dish with sauerkraut mixture.
Before putting pork chops on top, add chicken or beef broth or white wine.
Top with browned chops and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 375°.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Cook for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix lemon jello and milk.
Fold in other ingredients.
Pour in Pyrex dish and chill.
Cut into squares.

title: skunk deodorizer
directions: Mix together and bathe afflicted pets in solution.
Rinse with tap water.
This was developed in a science lab.
Skunk spray is composed of low molecular weight thiols similar to waste gas streams.
This is a household version of a chemical "scrubber."

title: chicken in orange sauce
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish arrange pieces of chicken.
Place carrot slices on top.
In small bowl combine orange and lemon juice, soy sauce, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Spoon over carrots and chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and baste with pan juices.
Sprinkle with onions.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes more.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut the washed vegetables into small pieces. Cut the beef into cubes and brown it in a pan. Put all ingredients together in a large pot. Cook the mixture over low heat until the meat is fully cooked and the vegetables are soft. Mix flour and hot water to make a paste. Add the paste slowly to thicken the stew.

title: pineapple spice cake
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon and nutmeg together.

Mix all other ingredients, except egg whites and nuts, then add nuts and fold in beaten egg whites after all other ingredients have been mixed. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: white bakery frosting
directions: Put shortening in mixer and mix well until soft and fluffy. Add other ingredients and beat at medium speed for at least 10 minutes.

title: momma jo's yellow squash
directions: Cut yellow squash into 1/2-inch rounds. Dice onion (1/4-inch) and place onions, water, sugar, pepper and chicken bouillon into medium stockpot.

Bring to a boil. Add squash and cook until just tender. Drain through a colander and place into a shallow pan containing cream cheese, butter and green chilies. Mix and serve immediately or refrigerate uncovered until cool. Once cool, cover.

title: vegetable medley(microwave)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine vegetables and water.
Cook, covered in microwave on 100% power, High, about 5 minutes or until almost tender, stirring once.
Add olives.
Or stir-fry vegetables with water and 2 tablespoons oil until vegetables are tender-crisp.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Slice onion in a large, buttered baking dish.
Put thinly sliced potatoes on top.
Place layers of crumbled ground beef, rice and kidney beans on top of potatoes.
Pour tomatoes over all this, using salt and pepper to taste.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Add the sugar, spices and cream of tartar to the boiling water.
Boil until a thread spins from the spoon.
Remove from heat and add the pecans and vanilla.
Stir until completely mixed. Turn onto wax paper and separate pecans.

title: scalloped chicken breast
directions: Blend together flour and seasonings.
Add chicken stock gradually and cook this mixture until it thickens to a gravy.

title: hamburger upside-down cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute onion in butter.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add chili powder, pepper and tomato.
Simmer 5 minutes. Combine flour and water; add to mixture and stir until thick. Spread evenly in 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
Prepare cornbread per package directions.
Spread onto hamburger mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Mix together in order listed.
Pour in greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: screaming eagle chili
directions: Brown beef, pork and onion.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
May serve over rice.
(Really different to serve over macaroni and cheese.)

title: mini pecan pies
directions: Mix all together and shape into 24 balls and press in tin.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, soup mix, egg, bread crumbs and water in a large bowl.
Knead until well blended.
Pinch off enough to make meatballs about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Roll into balls and place on an ungreased shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° (preheated) for about 30 minutes.
(Stir meatballs around after they begin to brown on top to prevent overcooking on one side.) Heat barbecue sauce until it begins to boil.
Add lemon juice and stir.
When meatballs are done, put them in a large bowl (drain off all excess grease).
Pour barbecue sauce over meatballs. Cover with foil and let stand for 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: vegetable salad
directions: This makes a large bowl of salad.

title: blue cheese bites
directions: Cut each biscuit into four pieces.
Arrange pieces on two greased 8 x 11 x 2 inch round baking pans.
Melt margarine; add cheese and stir to blend.
Drizzle cheese mixture over biscuits. Bake at 400° for 12 - 15 minutes.

title: white mountain salad
directions: Mix and chill for 1 hour.

title: flan
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Caramelize sugar by putting it in a heavy saucepan and cooking, without stirring, on medium-high heat until it begins to melt.
Reduce heat to low and stir until the caramel is golden brown.
Watch carefully or it will burn!
Pour caramel into a loaf pan and set aside (it's OK if it hardens).

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add sugar, egg and melted butter. Add flour 1 cup at a time. Bake in medium-size muffin tins at 350° until brown. Batter may be stored in refrigerator overnight or baked immediately. Makes 2 dozen rolls.

title: mom's spicy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, brown sugar, milk, beaten egg yolks, salt and spices in top of double boiler.
Cook about 10 minutes, stirring often.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve in pumpkin mixture. Pour into medium size bowl.
Chill just until beginning to set. Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time and beat well after each addition until meringue stands in soft peaks. Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill until firm enough to cut.

title: orange freeze
directions: Blend in blender until consistency of a milkshake.

title: breakfast delight
directions: Butter 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Spread croutons and cheese over bottom.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, onion, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add meat.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Stir in sugar and margarine.
Add eggs. Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add vanilla. Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate chips and 3/4 cup of coarsely chopped nuts over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir with eggs and salt to taste. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together sugar, vanilla, eggs and Crisco.
Sift together soda, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add vinegar, buttermilk and food coloring.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: pink cherry soda
directions: Chill all beverages thoroughly.
Pour beverages into punch bowl just before serving. Add ice cream in large scoops.
Makes 32 servings.

title: coconut pies
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine; let cool. Add sugar.
Mix lemon juice, vanilla, eggs and coconut.
Mix by hand.
Put in tart shells 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: cheese canapes
directions: Cut the bread into circles, diamonds or squares.
Butter them lightly and brown.
Cover each with a thick layer of the grated cheese to which the seasoning has been added.
Bake in the oven until the cheese is thoroughly melted and serve at once.

title: bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and eggs; beat well.
Add milk, then bran.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together, then add to first mixture.
Add raisins.
Place in greased muffin tins and bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 16 to 18 muffins.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Mix remaining ingredients, then add noodles.
Refrigerate.

title: baked chicken breasts with garlic & oregano
directions: Trim off any excess fat from the chicken.
Season generously on both sides with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 1/4 tsp. oregano over each piece and rub with crushed garlic.
Squeeze lemon juice over the chicken and coat lightly with olive oil.

title: grandma pat's breakfast bacon and sausage casserole
directions: Thoroughly cook sausage and bacon.
Drain off grease.
Crumble into bits.
Break bread into bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish. Spread sausage and bacon bits over bread.
Combine milk, eggs and cheese.
Pour over bread and meat.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Put chicken breast pieces in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with slices of Swiss cheese.
Mix soup and milk to make a sauce of pouring consistency; pour over the cheese.
Prepare dressing according to package directions.
Place over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13 pan. Bake German chocolate cake as directed on box. When cake is done, while hot, poke holes in cake, using end of a wooden spoon handle. Pour 1 can of Eagle Brand milk in holes, then pour 2/3 bottle of caramel ice cream topping. Let cake cool completely and top with Cool Whip. Crust 2 candy bars and sprinkle over top of cake. Refrigerate.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Ready pie crusts according to directions on box.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Top with pie crust.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: peanut butter cornflake candy
directions: Mix
in pan the syrup, sugar, butter and peanut butter. Heat slowly
and melt. Add cornflakes and mix well.
Spread in greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: angel biscuits
directions: In a 1-cup measure dissolve yeast in warm water.
In large bowl stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in butter until it is fine.
Stir in yeast mixture and enough of the buttermilk to make a fairly soft dough.
Turn out on pastry cloth; knead a few times to smooth dough.
With a stockinet covered rolling pin roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out with a round floured 2-inch cutter.
Place a few inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until golden brown, about 15 to 18 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Melt the chocolate over hot, not boiling, water. Then spread 2 tablespoons of the chocolate over bottom of cooled Cinnamon Meringue Shell. To remaining chocolate, add egg yolks and water; blend very thoroughly. Chill until mixture is thick.

title: chicken what-cha may call it
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Sprinkle over with rice.
Lay chicken over uncooked rice.
Mix in soup pot both soups and water.
Pour over chicken and bake 1 hour or until chicken is done at 350°.

title: homemade cough syrup
directions: Mix ingredients and heat.
Take one teaspoon for cough or hoarseness.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish and pour sauce over chicken; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done. Serve over rice.

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: In large frypan, cook onion, garlic, eggplant and mushrooms in olive oil over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, wine, carrot, parsley, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Boil to reduce sauce until it measures 5 cups; set aside.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash potatoes, peel and slice thinly (about 4 cups).
In greased 2-quart casserole, arrange potatoes in four layers.
Sprinkle each of the first 3 layers with 1 tablespoon onion, 1 tablespoon flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle top with onion, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Heat milk just to scalding and pour over potatoes. Cover and bake 30 minutes, uncovered.
Bake until tender.

title: janet's gingersnaps
directions: Cream the margarine, molasses and sugar.
Beat eggs well; add to creamed mixture.
Sift the flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to mixture.
Works up in a nice dough.
Roll dough in long rolls about 1 1/2 inches around.
Roll in wax paper and freeze.
Slice in thin slices and bake whenever you want at 350° until light brown.

title: baked pimento cheese
directions: Soak bread in water.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until set, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and spread over peanut butter mixture.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: bride's salad
directions: Prepare gelatin.
When partly congealed, add pineapple, cheese, nuts and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Pour into molds.
Chill to firm.
Top with whipped cream.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Bake one hour at 350° in Bundt pan.
Cool in pan until very cool.

title: strawberry banana cream pie
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water; let cool.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Add to the Jell-O mixture.
Whip the Pet milk, that has been chilled overnight in the refrigerator.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Pour 1-inch of cream cheese mixture into each of 2-inch tins lined with graham cracker crust.
Slice bananas over top.
Add another inch of cream mixture, then another layer of bananas, then another layer of cream mixture.
Top with whipped cream.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until brown.

title: northern beans taste like baked beans
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix gently, but well.
Place in slow cooker; put on slow heat overnight.

title: cornmeal biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and knead out into biscuits on floured board.
Place in greased pan.
Spray with Pam.
Bake in 450° oven until done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Long grain Louisiana rice, Gulf shrimp and Creole cooking make this subtly flavored New Orleans specialty.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix dressing, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate. Serves 6.

title: chewy squares
directions: Mix ingredients together.
May add dates, nuts, raisins or coconut to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream maple walnut muffins
directions: Grease and flour muffin tins.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Add egg, sour cream and maple extract. Stir just until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Let set 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix this together and put into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 9 1/2-inch pan.

title: peanut deviled ham ball
directions: Beat all ingredients, except peanuts, together until smooth and well blended.
Chill.
When firm enough to handle, shape into a ball.
Roll in peanuts to coat.
Chill 1/2 hour before serving with crackers.

title: stir and bake fruit cake
directions: Cut up all fruit.
Mix butter and sugar well.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour and cinnamon; mix well.
Add fruit and nuts; mix well.
Pour into a thick pan.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Dice potatoes and cheese.
Crumble bacon; add mayonnaise. Mix.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: christmas ornament cutouts
directions: For cookies, beat first 3 ingredients until fluffy.
Beat in eggs. Mix in combined remaining 4 ingredients.
Cover; chill 4 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll 1/4 of dough at a time 1/8-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut as desired using cookie cutters or glass.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. (For ornament hole, cut hole in cookie with drinking straw before baking.
Repeat immediately after baking if hole closes.)
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until edges are light golden brown.
Remove to wire rack; cool completely.

title: mix ahead pie crust
directions: Mix into small pebbles.
Put into a gallon glass jar until needed.
1 cup of mixture will make 1 (8-inch) shell.

title: banana split cake
directions: Place 2 cups graham cracker crumbs in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and margarine with electric mixer 15 minutes and pour over cracker crumbs. Pour drained pineapple over egg mixture.
Slice bananas on top of pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with maraschino cherries and pecan halves.

title: layered pumpkin cake
directions: Use one box of yellow cake
mix
and
remove one cup in separate bowl for the topping.
Combine
the
rest
of the dry mix with margarine and egg.
Press into
the
bottom
of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, milk, vanilla and almond extract; beat well.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Force through cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes; cool.
(If desired, sprinkle with sugar crystals.)
Makes approximately 72 cookies.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla; beat at medium speed until well blended. Add egg; beat until blended.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto sprayed cookie sheet.
Cook for 2 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer
lettuce	(torn or shredded), onion, bell pepper, ham and
sweet peas.
Spread salad dressing on top.
Sprinkle cheese.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add water and mix eggs in well.
Add rhubarb last and let stand until pie crust is ready.
Turn into a 10-inch pie shell and arrange lattice strips on top.
Bake at 400° until brown, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crackers in buttered casserole dish and cook at 300° about 30 minutes (until good and bubbly). Top with buttered Ritz crackers (crushed) and cook about 5 more minutes.
This can be mixed in advance and refrigerated.
Remove from refrigerator and let sit at room temperature for about 30 minutes before baking.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil water with sugar; let stand until cold.
Combine all and put in freezer.
Stir several times until frozen.
Fill glass 1/2 full and add soda.
Use with 7-Up, ginger ale or club soda.

title: festive carrot ring
directions: Combine carrots, crumbs, milk, cheese, butter, onion and seasonings.
Beat
eggs
until lightly puffy.
Fold into carrot mixture.
Pour
into
well-greased 1 1/2 quart ring mold.
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn out on a warm platter and fill center
with
cooked
peas.
Garnish outside of ring with parsley. Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: peas and carrots casserole
directions: Layer ingredients.
Pour tomato soup on top.
Add water to fill half of dish.
Adjust ingredients to fit your need.
Bake at 350° for approximately 3 hours.

title: campfire scramble
directions: Add potatoes to 2 tablespoons fat. Stir-fry until light brown. Beat 6 eggs and pour over potatoes.
Stir until cooked.
Sprinkle with bacon pieces and 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Microwave the first 4 ingredients on High for 7 to 8 minutes. Add butter and vanilla; microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Remove and add soda.
Stir and pour on a greased cookie sheet.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Sift 3/4 cup flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a bowl; add milk, oil and egg; beat until smooth to make a batter. Heat oil
1/2 inch deep in a heavy skillet or use a deep fryer.
Cut onions into 1/4 inch thick slices and separate into rings.
Put 1/2 cup flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a bag and drop in onion rings and
shake to coat.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Boil the jello and pineapple until jello is dissolved.
Cool completely. Add buttermilk and Cool Whip. Beat with mixer until completely mixed. Refrigerate.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, spices, soda and shortening.
Blend in the boiling water.
Beat eggs; pour in molasses and eggs.
Beat well.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool in pan before taking out of pan.

title: spicy mexican corn
directions: Drain picante sauce, reserving liquid.
Set vegetable mixture aside.
Measure reserved liquid, adding water if necessary, to measure 1/2 cup.
Combine reserved liquid and corn in saucepan. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes or until corn is tender.
Add vegetable mixture; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 1 minute.
Spoon into a serving bowl; sprinkle with cheese, covering until cheese melts.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: pork chop creole
directions: Sprinkle chops lightly with flour.
Cook in skillet with small amount of oil until brown; set aside to keep warm.
Brown onion in skillet; add tomatoes, seasonings and green pepper.
Return chops to sauce; cook slowly until thickened.
Place rice on platter; cover with chops.
Pour sauce over all.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: sweet citrus salad
directions: Place oranges, grapefruit and kiwi in bowl.
Toss with honey, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Combine greens, onions and oil in a salad bowl.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Partially cook the sweet potatoes in boiling water.
Cool and skin.
Cut potatoes in halves, lengthwise.
Grease a large baking dish with 1 tablespoon of margarine and place the potatoes in the dish.

title: three week coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, peppers, onions and sugar and mix well.
Mix oil, vinegar, salt and pour over cabbage mixture and stir until very well mixed.
Store in refrigerator in airtight container.
Let stand at least 2 to 3 days.
Flavor improves the longer it stands. Keeps well refrigerated.

title: apricot dessert(non-bake)
directions: Save out 2/3 of the crumbs.
Put rest in a large pan.
Cream together the powdered sugar and butter.
Add the egg yolks.
Beat the egg whites stiff and fold in. Add the vanilla. Run the cooked apricots through a sieve.
Put egg filling on top of crumbs.
Put apricots on top of egg filling.
Place the whipped cream on top of the apricots.
Refrigerate overnight before eating.

title: chocolate bavarian pie
directions: Line spring-form pan (sides first) with ladyfingers.
Combine sugar, water and chocolate bits.
Melt.
Let cool.
Beat egg yolks and add to chocolate bits mixture.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat whipped cream (put in fridge while doing whites).
Beat whites.

title: french onion soup
directions: Fry onions in butter only until golden and transparent.
Stir in flour and let it cook for 2 minutes.
Add salt and freshly ground pepper and pour in broth, stirring well.
Simmer gently for 15 minutes.
Fry slices of French bread in butter (usually one or two per person), place them in an ovenproof soup tureen or individual soup bowls and pour onions and broth over.
Sprinkle with thick layer of cheese.
Place in 350° oven until cheese has melted and serve immediately.

title: scripture cake
directions: Sift flour with salt, baking powder and spices; set aside. Cream butter with sugar, adding eggs one at a time.
Beat thoroughly.
Now, add flour mixture, alternating with water, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in honey, raisins and nuts.
Turn batter into buttered and floured 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; turn out on a rack to cool completely.

title: crisp green bean casserole
directions: Place drained green beans in casserole dish. Cover with mushroom soup.
Mix into beans.
Blend butter into corn flakes lightly.
Sprinkle over beans.
Cover.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix crumbs; take out crumbs for top.
Add 2 eggs and 1 cup buttermilk.
Mix; add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Makes 2 large or 3 smaller cakes.
Do not mix until smooth.
Batter will have small lumps.
Don't forget to grease and flour your pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apples and bacon
directions: Fry bacon.
Remove and set aside. Saute apples until tender in bacon drippings.
Sprinkle apples with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix and crumble bacon on top.
Serve hot!

title: encharitos
directions: Make soup as directed on can and add cheese and green chiles. Heat until cheese is melted.
Fill tortilla with chili and fold and top with cheese sauce.
You may also want to top with shredded lettuce, sour cream and hot sauce.
Tortilla chips on the side.

title: spinach empandadas
directions: Pastry:
In large bowl beat together cream cheese and butter with electric mixer until smooth.
Gradually beat in flour and salt.
Knead dough lightly by hand.
Cover dough with plastic wrap and refrigerate 3 hours.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 400°. In a medium bowl, combine apples, sugar and flour; set aside. In a double boiler, melt caramels with milk, stirring frequently. Add apple mixture. Spoon mixture into pie crust and top with nuts. Bake on preheated baking sheet for 25 minutes. Allow to cool 1 hour. Serve warm or cold. Garnish with whipped topping.

title: (unknown)
directions: Fry hamburger, adding seasoning of your choice.
Drain.
Put into electric fryer.
Put can of tomatoes and can of green beans with hamburger.
While that is cooking on medium heat, cook rice on stove.
Add 1 package taco mixture and water (according to directions on taco mixture) to hamburger.
When rice is done, put in with hamburger mixture.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Add 1 package Cheddar cheese to top.
Cover until melted.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare apples and slice thin.
Combine sugar, flour and spices; mix with apples.
Line the pie plate with pastry.
Fill with the apple mixture; dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Cover with top crust; sprinkle with sugar for better browning.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: swedish rusks (skorpor)
directions: Mix as a cake.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° in a long sheet pan (10 x 15-inch).
Cut into strips.
Remove from pan when cool and bake at 200° until light brown, for about 1 hour.
These are great with coffee in the morning!

title: french onion soup
directions: You will need 4 earthenware pots with lids (optional).

title: apple rings for garnishing pork
directions: Wash and cut apples crosswise into rings, leaving skin and core.
Boil sugar and water until syrup spins a thread; add coloring, then fruit.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Skim out rings separately and serve cold.
Yield:
12 rings.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Mix margarine and cheese.
Blend well.
Add flour and Rice Krispies.
Form into small balls.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut together flour, sugar, salt and Crisco until crumbly.
Add vinegar, beaten egg and cold water and blend well, using a fork. Dough will be moist.
Pat by small balls into lightly greased pie pans.
This dough can be rolled out too by using less water.
This is a never fail pie dough.
Makes 4 or 5 single crust pies.

title: swedish tea cake
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, egg yolk and flour. Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Dip in egg white, then roll in nuts. Place on cookie sheet and press down center with thumb. Bake 5 minutes in 350° oven. Remove and press down gently again. Bake 15 more minutes. Cool. Fill with jelly.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pie plate.
Beat the other ingredients until smooth. Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: mexican party mix
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix margarine and seasoning.
Pour over combined remaining ingredients except cheese balls.
Toss to coat. Place in 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheese balls.
Makes 12 cups.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth; set aside.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans; set aside.
Pour half of batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle half of sugar mixture over batter.
Repeat procedure. Gently swirl batter with a knife.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Drizzle glaze over cake and cool.
Cut into squares. Yields 15 to 18 servings.

title: rumaki
directions: Mix sugar, soy sauce, pineapple juice, garlic powder and ground ginger.
Soak water chestnuts and pineapple in mixture for 10 minutes.
Cut bacon slices in thirds.
