Roll water chestnuts and pineapple in bacon slice.
Secure with toothpick.
Pour soy sauce mixture over rolls.
Marinate for 1 hour (up to 24 hours okay). Bake at 450° until bacon is crisp, about 20 minutes.
Makes 50.

title: delicious beets
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salt and water and bring to a boil. Fill container of beets with this liquid.
They will keep indefinitely.

title: potato beef bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Simmer tomatoes, stock, celery, onion and parsley for 30 minutes.
Puree and strain.
Mix together cornstarch and butter. Stir into soup to thicken over medium heat.
Add brown sugar. (You can freeze the mixture at this point for a good soup base.) Otherwise, stir salt and pepper into very hot soup; add cream and mix.
Add some soup to egg yolk, mix and put into soup.
Serve.

title: frankteasers
directions: Cut franks in thirds.
Wrap with 1/2 slice bacon and poke with toothpick.
Place on foil lined cookie sheet.

title: spicy peanut noodles
directions: In a small saucepan, heat red pepper and oils over medium heat for two minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add honey, soy sauce and salt.
Combine with spaghetti.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Trim mushroom stems.
Wipe mushrooms with a cloth dipped in cold acidulated water (1 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice or distilled white vinegar to 2 cups water).
Place mushrooms in a heatproof bowl.

title: citrus crown cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease generously and flour 10-inch Bundt pan.
Combine marmalade, coconut and melted butter in small bowl.
Pour into pan.
Prepare cake following package directions. Pour batter over marmalade mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Invert cake onto serving plate.
Cool completely.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix altogether and store in refrigerator.
Pour over salad.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well. Add taco seasoning, tomato sauce and refried beans. Mix well. Pour into 9 x 13 baking dish. Spread sour cream on top and sprinkle with shredded cheese. Bake in a 400° oven until cheese melts and bubbles (15 to 20 minutes). Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Serve with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: mardi gras dinner
directions: Stir flour, pepper and 1/4 teaspoon salt into melted oleo in saucepan.
Mix until smooth.
Gradually add evaporated milk. Stirring constantly over medium heat, cook and stir until sauce is thickened.
Then add cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Place Minute rice, parsley, oregano, water and the remaining salt.
Stir to moisten all rice.
Place 2/3 of tomatoes.
Top with onion and tuna fish. Spread on cheese sauce.
Garnish with remaining tomato. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Soak apples in water overnight.
Chop apples.
Add molasses. Simmer gently 30 minutes.
Set aside.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring
pineapple
and sugar to full boil and add jello, stir until
dissolved.	 Add
softened	cream
cheese,	add ice water, celery and nuts.
Chill until partly congealed then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into bowl and refrigerate.

title: chicken consomme
directions: Brown chicken breasts in skillet or Dutch
oven
with 2 tablespoons
butter.
Add rice, consomme
and
mushroom
soup. Simmer for 1 hour on low heat.

title: chicken and capers
directions: Clean chicken.
Dredge in flour.
Melt butter in pan.
Brown chicken and remove to plate.
Add more butter to pan.
Add white wine and capers.
Bring to boil and simmer.
Put chicken back in pan to heat.
Can be served over linguini.
Enjoy!

title: turkey cheese puffs
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine.
Beat on medium speed until smooth.
Add milk.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in turkey and pepper. Unroll dough and separate into 4 rectangles; press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup turkey mixture in center of each dough rectangle.
Moisten edges of each rectangle with water.
Bring the 4 corners to the center over filling, pinching edges to seal. Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mini pizzas
directions: On a cookie sheet lay sliced muffins, cut side up.
Spoon sauce onto each muffin.
Sprinkle with cheese and toppings.
Bake at 350° to 400° until cheese melts.
Yield:
12 mini pizzas.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter, cream cheese, heavy cream and 4x sugar together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into baked graham crust and chill.
Top with Cool Whip!

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add syrup, well beaten eggs, vanilla and a pinch of salt to mixture.
Place nuts in pie shell and pour liquid into shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or plain.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Cream together softened cream cheese and sugar until well blended and fluffy.
Add eggs, vanilla and lemon juice.
Mix until well blended.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of paper liner and fill cupcake tin 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Yields 16 cupcakes.
When cooled, put cherry pie filling on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix soup, sour cream and milk, then pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until brown.

title: italian chicken
directions: Blend together salt and flour.
Roll in boneless breasts.
Put oil in skillet.
Add breasts, brown and remove.
Add chicken broth, tomato sauce, oregano and garlic salt.
Return chicken to heat.
Pour in mushrooms and simmer until tender.

title: p-nut crunch
directions: Boil cold water, sugar and Karo syrup to 250° and then add peanuts.
Stir until golden brown (3 to 5 minutes or to 290°). Now remove from heat and immediately add remaining ingredients, stirring in each individually.
The soda will cause the mixture to foam (takes about 30 seconds).
Then pour onto a greased baking sheet, spreading it around evenly.
Cool.
Break up and enjoy.

title: aunt frances' party crackers
directions: Stir together oil, dressing mix and dill weed.
Pour over crackers and stir to coat.
Let set several hours.
Stir again and enjoy!

title: old fashioned egg nog
directions: Heat milk.
Beat egg yolks with sugar until lemon colored. Add hot milk and stir constantly.
Add bourbon.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add to hot mixture.
Stir to mix in egg whites. Serve hot or chilled.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and garlic.
Add salt. Cover with cracked ice and let stand for 3 hours. Drain.
Combine all other ingredients and add cucumbers and onions.
Mix and bring to a boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake as directed and make 3 layers.

title: chocolate star cookies
directions: Sift the flour and soda.
Add milk, egg and vanilla.
Cream the shortening, peanut butter and sugars; combine all ingredients. Scoop out by teaspoonfuls; roll into balls and roll in sugar. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place Brach's chocolate star on each cookie, pressing firmly.
Bake for 3 more minutes.
Mmm!
Mmm! Good!

title: banana muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into muffin cups.
Bake until golden brown, 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Mix refried beans and taco seasoning.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise.
Mash avocados.
Chop tomatoes and onions.
Slice olives and shred cheese.
Layer the ingredients in the order given; chill.
Serve with nacho and corn chips.

title: lasagna
directions: Make 1 row sauce, 1 row lasagna, 1 row sauce and 1 row cheese. Cook for 1/2 hour.
Enjoy.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add milk gradually, stir and cook until thickened.
Season to taste.
Add potatoes and pimiento.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mississippi mud bars
directions: Combine butter, sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs.
Mix with electric mixer.
Add flour, vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Put batter in greased bar or jelly roll pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven.
Put marshmallow cream on top and let set a minute and then spread.
Cool.

title: taelerene casserole
directions: Brown onions in shortening, then ground beef.
Add tomato soup and water.
Add noodles and cook until tender.
Salt to taste. Also add black pepper and herbs.
Add corn (drain first).

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water (must not be hot water). Sift flour, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Add lump of lard and whole egg.
Mix together with the yeast water.
Do not beat.
Put in a greased pan.
Cover with oil paper and slide into refrigerator.
Make out rolls about 2 hours or 2 1/2 hours before needed.
Cook in oven at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute garlic and mushroom stem pieces in margarine.
Add sausage and cook.
Remove from heat and add dressing, usually about 1/2 cup.
Stuff each mushroom with mixture and top each mushroom with a small amount of margarine.
Place in oven on broil for about 3 to 5 minutes, until margarine melts and mushroom is soft.
Mixture can be made up ahead of time and refrigerated.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Blend eggs and shortening in mixer bowl. Add about half of the cake mix (dry mix).
Beat at medium speed on mixer until light and fluffy.
Add remaining cake mix.
Blend at low speed, scraping bowl often.
Form into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cookies will rise, then settle, but will be soft in center when done.
Allow to cool on baking sheet for 1 to 2 minutes before removing.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Dip eggplant in egg mixture and then in flour. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix frozen berries and juice together.
Add ginger ale. Serves 20.

title: spinach roll
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Stretch and flatten dough into a large baking sheet.
Place pepperoni down the center only of the dough.
Top with spinach mixture, then slices of American cheese. Cut 1-inch strips along both sides of spinach mixture.
Using 1 strip each on opposite sides, pick up and tie (similar to a shoe lace) and tuck excess dough underneath.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar together; add eggs, beating in 1 at a time.
Add vanilla and salt; mix thoroughly.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Pour boiling water over raisins and let stand a few minutes.
Drain well and add to egg mixture.
Add flour alternately with milk; add oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: holland cheese truffles
directions: Cream butter.
Combine butter, cheese and paprika.
Shape into small balls.
Roll half in crumbs and half in finely minced parsley.
Chill.
Makes 24.

title: one dish chicken and rice bake
directions: Prep Time: 5 minutes. Cook Time: 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and eggs; mix other ingredients and bake in uncooked crust for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crab louis in avocado halves
directions: Put yolk in mixing bowl; add mustard, Worcestershire sauce and vinegar.
Beat with wire whisk.
Add oil gradually, beating rapidly when thickened.
Add chili sauce, scallions and olives. Season with salt and pepper.
Put crab in mixing bowl; add half sauce.
Mix gently.
Split avocados in half and discard the pits. Pile equal portions of crab into avocado halves.
Spoon remaining sauce over.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: avocado pie
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pre-made Graham Cracker pie crust.
Refrigerate till ready to serve, then top with Whipped Cream or Cool Whip.

title: skillet steak 'n potatoes
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Cut into serving size pieces. Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge steak in flour mixture. Brown steak in hot oil.
Add broth and water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Turn meat and top with potatoes and onion.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: creamy strawberry pie in coconut crust
directions: Thinly slice 1 1/2 pints strawberries, reserving 1/2 pint. Combine with sugar.
Set aside until sugar dissolves.
Soften gelatin in water.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
Combine gelatin, strawberries and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream. Chill until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon.
Pour filling into coconut crust.
Chill at least 4 hours and garnish with remaining strawberries.
Makes 9-inch pie.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients stirring constantly until thickened.
Turn into shell and cover with meringue.
Bake at 350° until brown. Cool and enjoy!

title: raspberry mint punch
directions: Combine in punch bowl all ingredients.
Serves 14.

title: deep-fried okra pods
directions: Parboil okra pods 8 to 10 minutes with salt, lemon juice and water to cover. Drain okra and rinse in cool water; drain well. Coat in a mixture of cornmeal, flour, baking powder, onion powder, salt and cayenne pepper.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add salt, baking soda, flour, vanilla and persimmon pulp.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: creamy orange-pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 cup; heat to boil.
Add boiling liquid to jello and cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Cool, stirring occasionally.
Fold cream, carrot and pineapple into cooled gelatin.
Pour into mold.
Chill.

title: quick chicken stir-fry
directions: In skillet, cook chicken in oil until brown.
Only use 1/4 tablespoon oil.
In remaining oil (1 tablespoon), fry vegies. Make sure oil is hot before you add vegies.
Add ginger and garlic to vegies.
Fry until tender-crisp.
Add soup, soy sauce and vinegar.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortenings.
Add eggs.
Add flour and milk alternately, starting and ending with flour.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: tuna cones
directions: You will also need an ice cream scoop and bowl.

title: brambles
directions: Combine pastry mix with cold water and divide into two portions.
Roll one portion into a large rectangular sheet. Place on cookie sheet.
Spread with cooled raisin mixture.
Roll other pastry.
Place on top of raisin mixture.
Turn a bit of lower crust up over edge of upper crust; flute edge all around. Take a paring knife and gently mark off the top crust into 24 squares.
(Don't cut through pastry.)
Use a fork to prick two sets of holes in each square.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from oven.
Allow to cool a few minutes, then cut the 24 Brambles and place on rack to cool.

title: pizza goes bananas
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Prepare brownie mix as directed by package.
Spread on greased round pizza pan and bake 16 -19 minutes (don't over bake).
Cool. Combine cream cheese, brown sugar and peanut butter until smooth.
Spread mixture over brownie leaving about 1/2 inch on the edge. Chop candy and peanuts and sprinkle on top.
Slice bananas and place on top. In microwave, cook oil and chocolate chips on high for 1 1/2 minutes until chocolate is melted.
Stir and drizzle on pizza.
Cut with pizza wheel in slices or squares.

title: zucchini-tomato-noodle soup
directions: Combine zucchini and water in a Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat until partially done.
Cook and stir onion in hot butter in a small skillet over medium heat until tender.
Add onion mixture, tomatoes, bouillon cubes, garlic, seasoning, salt and pepper to zucchini mixture.
Simmer until tender.
Add noodles; heat through.
Serve with garlic bread.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick sticky buns
directions: Cut each biscuit in half and form each piece into a ball. Combine sugar, cinnamon and pecans in small bowl.
Dip each biscuit half into butter, then into sugar mixture.
Place in greased 8-inch cake pan.
Mix remaining butter and sugar and spoon over biscuit balls.
Drizzle corn syrup over all.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: ham and potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine potatoes, ham and onion in a greased 1-quart casserole; set aside.
In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat; stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add cheese, salt and pepper; stir until cheese melts.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease a 3-quart oblong baking dish, layer half of the rice, chicken, celery and remaining rice.
In a medium bowl, mix water, soups and sherry until smooth.
Pour over rice.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake for 2 hours or until chicken and rice are tender.
Lift chicken to surface of rice mixture.
With a fork, stir rice and sauce lightly around edges to blend.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika and almonds.
Garnish with celery leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add soda, flour and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon stew
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in a little water until tender.
Add other ingredients.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Bring milk, salt, butter and sugar to a boil.
Mix cornstarch with water.
When all the lumps are dissolved, mix in egg yolks. Pour into boiling milk mixture.
Remove pan from heat and whisk until thick and smooth.
Now whisk in peanut butter.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover and refrigerate until cold, then top with whipped cream or meringue.

title: cinnamoned barbecue sauce
directions: Saute the onions and celery in the butter until soft.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well. Simmer slowly, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Good served with a roasted whole chicken or cut up fryer, flank steak, spareribs or lamb chops.
Makes 3 cups sauce.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in 8 x 8-inch Tupperware container. First, refried beans, then mix cream cheese and sour cream in a separate bowl. Spread mixture on refried beans.
Next put the taco sauce, then place lettuce, onion and tomatoes.
The last layer is cheese. When serving, place chips on the side.

title: lemon sorbet
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add water and ice and stir until ice is melted.
Stir in lemon and rind; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze until crystals form, about 1 inch from edge of pan, 1 to 2 hours.
Spoon mixture into chilled blender or food processor and blend at high speed until smooth, about 30 seconds. Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and freeze firm, 6 hours or overnight.

title: betty's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray cookie sheet
with Pam and line with 1 layer of graham crackers.
Combine sugar and butter in small pan.
Bring to a boil, boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over crackers and cover with chopped nuts.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cut up apples in small chunks.
Mix eggs, sugar and oil together.
Mix in apples and all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lil's crawfish or shrimp fettucine
directions: Melt magarine in large saucepan.
Add onions and bell peppers and cook for about 20 minutes.
Add flour, stirring frequently, for about 15 minutes.
Add parsley and crawfish tails (shrimp) and cook, covered, for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Add cream, cheeses and garlic; cover, stirring often, until cheeses melt.

title: carolina fish
directions: Cut up fillets of your favorite fish.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup and dashes of Worcestershire sauce.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: turnip greens
directions: Place meat and water in a large pot along with salt, pepper and sugar.
Boil until meat is almost cooked.
Remove from heat. Cut roots off of turnip, peel and slice.
Remove stems from turnip top.
Put roots and tops together and wash several times. Place in pot with meat and cook 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add more water if needed.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: show-off vegetable plate
directions: Steam pea pods or cauliflower head until done.
Drain and season to taste with butter and salt.
Brown mushrooms in 1/4 cup butter and then add tomatoes and olives.
Cover and steam through. Remove from heat just before tomato skins pop.
Salt to taste.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Three-fourths
box Blue cheese crackers, crumbled, can also be used for topping.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the cranberries and the sugar together.
Let stand for 3 to 4 hours.
Drain the pineapple. Add the marshmallows and nuts. Mix together with the cranberries. Fold in the Cool Whip. Chill and serve.

title: mom's bean casserole
directions: Saute onion, bacon and sirloin together; drain well.
In a large pan, mix meat mixture with beans and mustard.
Sprinkle sugar and ketchup on top, then mix together entire casserole. Just prior to baking, sprinkle vinegar lightly over top of mixture.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Heat Karo and sugar to a boil, add peanut butter, let melt. Pour over cornflakes and nuts, mix well.
Spoon by tablespoon quickly onto wax paper.
Shape with hands (buttered) if needed.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shred dried beef in blender.
Save 1/2 cup or more to roll balls in.
Combine ingredients and form into two balls.
Roll in shredded beef.
Refrigerate.

title: apple squares
directions: Cream margarine, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add beaten egg and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add apple and walnuts. Press into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar and cut into squares when cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, Karo, sugar, margarine and vanilla in a large bowl. Blend well.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red raspberry dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 1/4 cup sugar together.
Bake at 400° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix first mixture with 1 cup sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
After this is partially set, top with jello, water and raspberries, mixed together.

title: old-fashioned egg salad
directions: In bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in eggs and celery.
Cover and chill.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: santa fe casserole
directions: In medium skillet, brown meat and stir until crumbly; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning; blend well.
In small bowl, combine broth and flour.
Add to meat mixture; bring to a boil to slightly thicken liquid.
Stir in sour cream and chilies; blend well.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch lightly greased glass baking dish place 1/2 chips, 1/2 of beef mixture, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 green onions.
Layer again with remaining ingredients ending with green onions.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: coconut loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a very large bowl.
Put into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 225° for 2 hours or until brown on top.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs. Spread 2 cups batter into greased, 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: date and walnut loaf
directions: Combine dates, walnuts and shortening.
Add boiling water and cold water.
Stir in sugar, egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add gradually to date mixture.
Pour into greased, large loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at
for	1 1/2 hours.
When cake is done, cut into squares and make this icing.

title: enchilada casserole #1
directions: *Fritos may be used instead of tortillas.

title: velvet chicken with mushrooms(ginger chicken)
directions: Marinate chicken pieces in soy sauce, pepper and 1 tablespoon oil for 10 minutes.
Heat remaining oil in skillet, add fresh garlic and fresh ginger; cook slightly (burns easily).
Add cornstarch and cook slightly.
Add chicken and cook.
Add about 2 cups water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and cooked.
Add mushrooms.
Serve over rice.

title: boiled collards
directions: Boil ham hock in 4-quart pot about 30 minutes.
Add greens, salt, pepper, bacon drippings and sugar.
Cook 45 minutes or until greens are tender.
Remove from pot and cut into bite size pieces. Liquid is very good with hot cornbread and onions.

title: granola(cold cereal)
directions: Heat oatmeal 10 minutes in a 250° oven.
Combine coconut, wheat germ and cinnamon with oatmeal.
Add together honey, oil and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients until coated.
(This can all be mixed and baked on a large cookie sheet!) Bake 15 to 20 minutes, stirring often.
Add cashews and sunflower seeds.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Toss raisins in brown sugar and add.
Store in airtight container.
A neat gift idea!

title: jubilee jumbles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly; stir in milk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda and stir in batter. Blend in walnuts.
Chill 1 hour. Heat oven to 375°; drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with butter icing.

title: sweet soup
directions: Soak fruit in a covered kettle overnight.
Cook slowly for at least 45 minutes, adding sugar and tapioca.
This should have a thick consistency, but if too thick, add water.
Serve hot or cold.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Combine the first five ingredients.
Sprinkle with salt and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain and add sugar and enough vinegar to cover ingredients.
Boil 15 to 20 minutes. Put in cans and seal.

title: peach pie delight
directions: Mix and pour in pie shell. Chill.

title: indian roasted corn
directions: Remove large outer
husks
from
corn.
Turn back inner husks and remove silk.
Pull
husks
back
over
corn and tie. Dissolve salt in enough cold water to cover corn.
Soak corn 1 hour. Drain.
Grill corn over hot coals for 15 to 20 minutes, turning frequently.
Serve dripping with butter.

title: "joyful" oat bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients and wet ingredients separately, then mix both together.
Mix until moist.
Do not overmix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cheesy mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until done, then mash.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, butter, seasonings and onion.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: pecan balls
directions: Sift flour and salt together. Cream butter and sugar. Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly. Roll in small balls and bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 275°. Roll in powdered sugar when removed from oven and again when they are cold.

title: super roast
directions: Rub all sides of meat with A-1 sauce.
Place in a roasting pan lined with heavy-duty foil.
Be sure foil is big enough to seal around roast.
Sprinkle onion soup over meat.
Add vegetables; spoon soup over all.
Seal foil.
Bake at 350° until meat is tender.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Prepare cornbread according to package directions.
Pour batter into well-greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Place frankfurters on batter.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes until done.

title: "sad sacks"
directions: Blend sugar, Bisquick, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake! When pan is removed from oven, the center of the cookies will sink in.
Cool well before cutting.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Crumble Doritos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread cooked chicken over Doritos crust.
Layer onion, then bell pepper. In separate bowl mix soups and Ro-Tel.
Pour over bell peppers. Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° until onion is done.

title: annie d's bacardi rum cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts on bottom of greased tube or Bundt pan.
Mix remaining cake ingredients; pour over nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Cool.
Invert on serving plate.

title: clam dip
directions: Soften cheese and blend until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill and serve with crackers or chips.

title: potatoes con queso
directions: Melt butter, add flour whisk until smooth.
Add milk and cook until thickened.
Stir in 1
1/2 c. cheese.
Add pimento, green chiles, jalapeno pepper and salt.
Place half of potato slices in 2 qt. greased baking dish.
Top with w/half of cheese mixture. Repeat layers.
Bake, covered at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. Uncover and bake 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 c. cheese.
Bake 5 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat at low speed until smooth and creamy.
Bake in buttered baking dish (10-inch pie plate) at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Add flour, sugar, milk, egg yolks and salt to raisins.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown in oven.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook Sweet 'N Low, water and cornstarch until clear.
Add Jell-O and strawberries.
Put into 2 baked pie shells.
Top with Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lemon lush
directions: First Layer:
Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown (20 to 25 minutes).
Cool.

title: golden chicken lasagne
directions: Melt butter.
Add mushrooms, peppers and onions.
Saute 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken soup, milk, pimentos and basil.
Arrange 1/2 noodles layered in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Top with layers of 1/2 of the sauce, 1/2 of the cottage cheese, 1/2 of chicken, 1/2 Cheddar cheese and 1/2 Parmesan cheese.
Add remaining noodles and repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 52 to 60 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.
Delicious!!

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Add drained corn, salt and black pepper; mix well.
Put in casserole dish that has been buttered, add remaining butter to corn, squash mixture.
Cover with slices of American cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Take out and stir until cheese is mixed well with other ingredients.

title: maryland crab soup
directions: Cook a beef soup bone for 1 hour for taste.
Take soup bone out and add all ingredients except crab meat.
Cook over medium heat for 30 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Then add crab meat and heat on medium heat for about 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate pie
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl.
Add pudding mix; beat with whisk until well blended (1 minute).
Let stand 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip and chopped candies.
Spoon into crust and freeze.
Remove from freezer; let stand 10 minutes to soften before serving.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: basic yeast dough
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, sugar and yeast in large bowl.
Heat water, milk and margarine until warm and margarine is melted.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well . Add rest of flour and mix well.
Knead 5 minutes until dough is smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and shape into desired shapes.
Cover.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° in well-greased pans.
Can be used for bread, rolls, cinnamon rolls, etc.

title: beach brew
directions: Combine all ingredients when ready to serve.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: sour cream drop cookies(makes 6 dozen)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add beaten egg. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour cream and vanilla. Add raisins, nuts, etc. Drop from teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes and enjoy!

title: mom's potato soup
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Cover with water and boil for 30 minutes.
Cut onion into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add to potatoes and boil an additional 15 minutes.
Drain all water from potatoes and add milk, butter, salt and pepper.
When thoroughly hot, add cheese and stir until melted.
Pour into individual bowls and garnish with crumbled bacon.
This soup is very tasty but is definitely not for those who need to watch their cholesterol intake!

title: 1900 grandma's mincemeat
directions: Grind first 5 ingredients together.
Add salt to taste.
Then add remaining ingredients.	Simmer until apples and raisins are done.
Use for pie or cookies.
May be canned or frozen.

title: ham and cheese noodle casserole
directions: Cook onions in butter.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This freezes well before or after baking.

title: sue's oven goulash
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add onion and cook until tender. Drain.
Stir in all ingredients except cheese.
Combine with macaroni.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: With mixer, cream sugar, butter and cream cheese well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla. At a slower speed, add flour a little at a time.
Pour into large greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Put cake upside down to cool.

title: pasta shrimp salad
directions: Cook pasta shells as directed and mix in all other ingredients.
May be served chilled.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Cook beans.
Cut bacon in 1/2 inch pieces.
Saute lightly in medium skillet.
Add onions; saute until onion is tender and bacon is browned.
Combine in large bowl the beans, onion, bacon, tomato sauce, brown sugar, dry mustard, 1/2 teaspoon salt, oregano and 1/2 cup water.
Blend well.
Turn into 2 to 2 1/2 quart shallow baking dish.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: old fashion cream pie
directions: Cook all together.
Put into a baked pie shell.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and refrigerate.

title: luncheon asparagus
directions: Melt butter; add flour and cook for several minutes.
Add milk gradually, stirring until thickened; add cheese and allow to melt. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Put asparagus on muffins; pour sauce over this and sprinkle with bacon pieces.
Sherry may be added to sauce.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl of electric mixer, beat first 5 ingredients on medium speed until light and fluffy.

title: spaghetti ala carbonara
directions: Heat the oil and butter in a skillet.
Add the pancetta/bacon. Saute until golden.
Lift from fat with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Cook the pasta in plenty of boiling water until al dente or firm to the bite, about 10 minutes; drain.

title: utterly deadly southern pecan pie
directions: Boil sugar and syrup together 2 to 3 minutes.
Beat eggs, not too stiff.
Pour in slowly the hot syrup.
Add butter, vanilla and pecan meats.
Bake in raw pie shell at 350° or until set.

title: khoresht-e baademjan(eggplant stew)
directions: Place peeled and sliced eggplant on a platter and put salt on both sides.
Set aside for two hours.

title: iceberg pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers.
Cover with water and sprinkle with lime.
Let soak for 24 hours (use plastic pot suitable for lime). Wash pickles one time each hour for 4 hours in clear water.
After fourth washing, mix vinegar and sugar and pour over pickles.
Put pickling spice in small sack and drop into pickles.
Cover and let set overnight.
Take sack of spices out of pickles and let pickles boil for 1 hour over medium heat.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Makes 8 to 9 pints.
